<title>Feb_1993: Women in the church</title>
<h1>Women in the church</h1>
Lisa Parry (<i>parry@peter.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Feb 1993 12:33:33 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#146">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#146">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#146">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#146">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0147.html">Michael Merginio: "Can Satan Read Minds???"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0145.html">Lisa Parry: "Re: Can Satan read my mind? (Or yours?)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Time to throw in two cents.<br>
<p>
I realize that women may not have all the power some want in the<br>
church everywhere, but I think decided leaps and bounds have been<br>
made.  In my current church (Kalamazoo) women are leaders in many<br>
areas, especially outreach programs, and are often up front talking<br>
about that and encouraging others to get involved.<br>
<p>
I attend a Sabbath School class that is taught by a lady and a man<br>
(alternate weeks) and there are at least two other classes in the<br>
church taught by women.  <br>
<p>
As for singles, my church does have a group for that (it's small at<br>
the moment - only about 6, but we have fun going on outings and planning<br>
interesting things to do).<br>
<p>
Single parents?  There is a small group in the church, and babysitting<br>
and support group is catered to as much as possible (though I must admit<br>
this program is relatively new).<br>
<p>
Women's groups?  There's a bundle going on around.  Personally they don't<br>
interest me, so I haven't attended any, but they're there (maybe this is<br>
from influence of Andrews University, which is within 100 miles?).<br>
<p>
This may not please everyone, but effort is being made to keep everyone<br>
included and not feeling lonely or overlooked.  Not 100% success, but<br>
not much else to do but try...<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"If God is for us, who can be against us?"            Lisa Parry
--Romans 8:31, last sentence                   parry@andrews.edu
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
