<!-- body="start" -->
To all those SDAnetters,<br>
<p>
I, too, have wondered if Satan can read minds, and although I still would<br>
like to do more research, I think there are at least two ways that one<br>
could take this discussion.<br>
	1. Being created by God, that he was not given the power to read<br>
		the minds of others.<br>
-OR-<br>
	2. Although created by God, he and all the other angels were<br>
		given the power to read the minds of the other beings.<br>
<p>
I personally believe that God did not give Satan that power to read<br>
minds, although over the observation of your life &amp; mine, he has been<br>
able to figure out what temptations would work best on you &amp; me.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Wishing You all the Best in Life,
Michael B. Merginio
merginim@andrews.edu
<p>
James White Library, Berrien Springs, MI 49104-1300, (616) 471-6344
=====================================================================
I believe that in our world, there is only one rule that everyone
	should follow, and that is - TELL IT LIKE IT IS! 
	The truth may hurt, but lies hurt even more.
=====================================================================
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
