<title>Feb_1993: Thinking man's church?  or "The church with the Truth"</title>
<h1>Thinking man's church?  or "The church with the Truth"</h1>
<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i><br>
<i>Mon, 15 Feb 93 09:43:59 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#151">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#151">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#151">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#151">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0152.html">Steven Timm: "Re:  Women on women"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0150.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Women's issues"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0163.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Thinking man's church?  or "The church with the Truth""</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Cheryl]<br>
<i>&gt; Just wanted to respond to what woody said:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;         "The Adventist church is a thinking mans church."</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; . . . . . . . .</i><br>
<i>&gt; . . . . . . . .</i><br>
<p>
A friend of mine, who is not SDA, commented that ALL churches have their<br>
own way of contriving scripture to fit the the doctrines of their<br>
church.  He says he goes to a Pentecostal church because he enjoys the<br>
fellowship and the hi-tech program even though there is a lot of their<br>
theology that he does not agree with, including speaking in tongues.<br>
This suits him just fine because he has been taught that "love" is all<br>
that counts, i.e. being a loving Christian == Salvation.  So is of no<br>
concern to him that he differs on so many points of theology.  He finds<br>
that SDA theology comes the closest to his reading of the Bible, but<br>
but his wife thinks "SDAs are too legalistic".<br>
<p>
I have always thought of the SDA church as being the church for people<br>
who eagerly want to search out the church that comes the closest<br>
possible to teaching what the Bible teaches.  EGW certainly points us<br>
in that direction.  A people who are eager to follow the word of God<br>
regardless of the cost, to obey God rather than man, to do His<br>
commandments because we love Him.<br>
<p>
Perhaps, when Woody said "thinking man's church" he meant those who<br>
want to be serious students of the Bible and obedient to what they<br>
find rather than a church for intelectual theologians.<br>
<p>
The Catholic church claims to be a thinking man's church in that<br>
doctrine and conscience are ruled by the ordained ecclesiastic<br>
"thinking men" of the hierarchy.  The rest of the church are the<br>
peasents.  We are a thinking man's church in the Protestant sense that<br>
calls for church and state to be subservient to each man's<br>
conscience, made subservient to the Bible.  At least that is the<br>
church that was founded several years ago.  While other churches<br>
have their prophets that point their followers away from the Bible,<br>
or at least to distrust it in so many ways; the SDA church has a<br>
prophet who urges its membership to an ever deeper study of the Bible.<br>
Just as the Old Testament authenticates the New Testament.  So the<br>
entire Bible authenticates EGW as a prophet.  The BIble is our<br>
final creed, authority and authenticator of prophets, preachers and<br>
evangelists.  If they speak not accordingly, there is no light in them.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
