Patriarchs and Prophets p54  (Eve and the serpent)  "As if he [Satan] were<br>
able to discern the workings of her mind, he addressed her: 'Yea, hath God<br>
said, Ye shall not eat of every tree of the garden?'  Eve was surprised and<br>
startled as she thus seemed to hear the echo of her thoughts."<br>
