<title>Feb_1993: Seminary</title>
<h1>Seminary</h1>
Lisa Parry (<i>parry@peter.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 16 Feb 1993 18:10:18 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#169">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#169">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#169">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#169">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0170.html">Steven Timm: "Question on Great Controversy in Mexico"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0168.html">Steven Timm: "More Women's Issues"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0165.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: Women and the SDA Church"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; But you speak as if there is a large number of women clammering to get it but</i><br>
<i>&gt; being denied this access.  I can believe there are some but not large numbers.</i><br>
<i>&gt;  If you can substantiate these claims with even a statement that you know or</i><br>
<i>&gt; have heard of x number of women that have been denied, I'd like to know about</i><br>
<i>&gt; it.  I don't think the seminary denies a disproportionate number of women to</i><br>
<i>&gt; men.  I am not saying that it doesn't happen...i just would be surprised.</i><br>
<p>
Just a personal experience.  I attend Andrews University.  During my<br>
Youth Ministry class last quarter, I visited the seminary a few times<br>
for research material and advice.  I consulted with two professors,<br>
and BOTH, in the process of the conversation brought it around to ask<br>
if I had any interest in going toward pastoral ministry.  Both were<br>
very encouraging on the issue, and tried their best to convince me.<br>
When I brought up the idea that women are not well accepted in that<br>
field, they stressed the fact that the church can't get used to it<br>
if women aren't out there to break tradition.  Now I still plan to<br>
go into teaching, not preaching, but I don't believe that the seminary<br>
professors are out to keep women out of the ministry.  The message<br>
I got from the ones I talked to was - we're in the last days.<br>
If the Lord is calling you into ministry, follow the calling and<br>
we'll do all we can to support that.  <br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"If God is for us, who can be against us?"            Lisa Parry
--Romans 8:31, last sentence                   parry@andrews.edu
</pre>
