Is it fair to say that the WASP representation at the GC session effectively<br>
voted *for* women's ordination, while the Hispanic and Black representation<br>
didn't? I heard that the vote would have been "yes" if it were not for strong<br>
opposition from the non-WASP cultures.<br>
<p>
If so, it is another good argument for a more congregational approach to<br>
things, rather than insisting that an SDA church is an SDA church no matter<br>
where you are or who you're with.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
