<title>Feb_1993: Re: Women's issues (Clarification for overseas people)</title>
<h1>Re: Women's issues (Clarification for overseas people)</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Feb 1993 00:28:59 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#174">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#174">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#174">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#174">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0175.html">Malachi Robertson: "Satan and Minds"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0173.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "GC and ordination of women"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve,<br>
Could I get you to briefly fill me in on a couple of things:<br>
	a) what is Libertarianism all about?<br>
[Libertarianism is a minor party in the USA and elsewhere which favors<br>
minimal government intrusion in people's lives.  Religious liberty is <br>
promoted, but so is legalization of drugs, pornography, etc.  Also <br>
the Libertarians favor major cutting of government spending.  In the <br>
last US election they got between 2 and 3 percent of the vote in some races.]<br>
<p>
	b) what kind of arguments were used to keep black etc people<br>
	out of Church office etc?<br>
[Many of the same ones as are currently being used against women.<br>
"They prefer to let whites manage their affairs.  They're not capable<br>
of managing themselves.  Some church members aren't ready for this to happen.<br>
They're inferior in capacity, etc, etc, etc......"  SCT]<br>
<p>
<p>
Thanx<br>
	Raylene<br>
