Hi all,<br>
<p>
<p>
I just have a very short question for us to consider. I would like some<br>
answers regarding this question.<br>
<p>
Why is it that neither Jesus nor the disciples never addressed the current <br>
social issues of their day (eg slavery, infringement of human rights etc). These<br>
issues were not petty or irrelevant yet Jesus never addressed them. Instead<br>
of addressing them (Jesus could have effectively addressed various of these)<br>
He taught the people to live with them, and even consider them hidden blessings.<br>
<p>
<p>
Why ?<br>
<p>
<p>
If He didn't and He is our example then to what extent should we ?<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
