<title>Feb_1993: Congregational Adventism (or Adventist Congregationalism)</title>
<h1>Congregational Adventism (or Adventist Congregationalism)</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Feb 1993 01:57:53 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#181">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#181">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#181">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#181">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0182.html">Steven Timm: "LDS women"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0180.html">Steven Timm: "Investigative Judgement"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Tony suggested that the womens issues are another reason towards having <br>
more local governance of churches.  Let me inform those of you who<br>
haven't heard yet:  <br>
<p>
Congregational Adventism is here!  **<br>
<p>
<p>
(** Not valid in Michigan and where otherwise prohibited)<br>
<p>
The policies of this church are still uniformly set, but not uniformly <br>
enforced anymore.  Pastors and boards have much opportunity to find<br>
latitude within the "guidelines."  We are entering the post-institutional<br>
stage of Adventism, when the only SDA institution a member will contact<br>
during his or her lifetime is his/her local congregation.  For 50-75%<br>
of our youth this is already the case.<br>
<p>
Congregational Adventism is not a boon to everyone, though.  At the last<br>
yuppie listening session in the Pennsylvania Conference, I realized that<br>
although Jerry Page, president of that conference, is a Baby Boomer himself,<br>
as was the recent secretary of that conference, and our local pastor in <br>
Pittsburgh is also a boomer, this has not translated into the change young <br>
people would like to see in the churches of Pennsylvania.  Congregations<br>
are more likely to impede progress than to rush ahead on their own.<br>
These same people would, however, most likely follow along with reform<br>
were orders to come from the top.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
