<title>Feb_1993: Re: Jesus and social issues</title>
<h1>Re: Jesus and social issues</h1>
McCluskey G (<i>glenm@usl.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Feb 93 10:48:38 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#185">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#185">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#185">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#185">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0186.html">Stan Macasieb: "The World Church"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0184.html">Steven Timm: "Board status"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0201.html">Edgar Vega: "Jesus and social issues"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; I just have a very short question for us to consider. I would like</i><br>
<i>&gt; some answers regarding this question.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Why is it that neither Jesus nor the disciples never addressed the</i><br>
<i>&gt; current social issues of their day (eg slavery, infringement of human</i><br>
<i>&gt; rights etc). These issues were not petty or irrelevant yet Jesus never</i><br>
<i>&gt; addressed them. Instead of addressing them (Jesus could have</i><br>
<i>&gt; effectively addressed various of these) He taught the people to live</i><br>
<i>&gt; with them, and even consider them hidden blessings.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Why ?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; If He didn't and He is our example then to what extent should we ?</i><br>
<p>
Well, human nature has probably not changed since Jesus's time, and<br>
it's also highly likely that there were social issues in abundance<br>
back then.  Perhaps one way of answering this question is to look at<br>
ourselves and see how we react.<br>
<p>
This newsgroup is one example of reactions -- more heat than light on<br>
issues such as the ordinatin of women, abortion, last fall's<br>
presidential election, and so on.<br>
<p>
Another example is the tendency to take sides and denigrate people on<br>
the other side -- I see this in myself in the social issues I've<br>
followed over the years.<br>
<p>
I used to think when I was younger that people could be logically<br>
convinced that particular positions are right.  Now I realize it's<br>
more a matter of changing what is in the heart.  I think that is why<br>
Jesus did what He did.<br>
<p>
Glen McCluskey<br>
glenm@usl.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
