<title>Feb_1993: Re: Social issues</title>
<h1>Re: Social issues</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>18 Feb 1993 15:31:46 +1100</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#198">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#198">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#198">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#198">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0199.html">AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "ordained vs not ordained duties"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0197.html">Drew Corrigan: "WCoG and SDAs"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
..what does the Lord require of you? To do justice, to love mercy, and<br>
to walk humbly with your God.<br>
<p>
Some would argue that the entire ceremonial law was set up to ensure<br>
that people treated each other with fairness and justice as much as<br>
possible at the time. Much of the writings of the minor prophets was<br>
directed at the issue of justice (eg Amos, Micah).<br>
<p>
Jesus' treatment of women and of gentiles was way off the accepted norm<br>
in his society. He may not have been one of those single-minded activists,<br>
but he was still a champion of human rights.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
