<title>Feb_1993: Jesus and social issues</title>
<h1>Jesus and social issues</h1>
Edgar Vega (<i>edgarv@trin.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 18 Feb 93 15:04:07 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#201">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#201">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#201">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#201">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0202.html">Dave Thomas: "Re: Women and the SDA Church"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0200.html">AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "Des Ford"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0185.html">McCluskey G: "Re: Jesus and social issues"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Ruben ask:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Why is it that neither Jesus nor the disciples never addressed the current </i><br>
<i>&gt; social issues of their day (eg slavery, infringement of human rights etc). These</i><br>
<i>&gt; issues were not petty or irrelevant yet Jesus never addressed them. Instead</i><br>
<i>&gt; of addressing them (Jesus could have effectively addressed various of these)</i><br>
<i>&gt; He taught the people to live with them, and even consider them hidden blessings.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; If He didn't and He is our example then to what extent should we ?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
Ruben :<br>
<p>
Jesus objective was not to change the world but to save the sinner,<br>
teaching us by example and word how we should live here and what we<br>
should look for.<br>
<p>
For the contrary, WE try to fix or change the church and those who are<br>
part of it.   The objective of Satan is just to distract our attention<br>
to subjects other than salvation.<br>
<p>
The SDA church grew a lot (in knowledge and number) when people were <br>
worried about knowing better the Scriptures rather than who is at the<br>
pulpit or what gender does mi pastor belongs to?  The SDA church in USA<br>
is not growing as much as before because our priorities have changed.<br>
<p>
Remember the church is just what we are.<br>
<p>
Edgar<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
