<title>Feb_1993: women's ordination and the Will of God</title>
<h1>women's ordination and the Will of God</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 18 Feb 93 18:17:52 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#205">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#205">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#205">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#205">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0206.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Des Ford"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0204.html">Steven Timm: "Send in directory information"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I'll be quite open and confess that I'm a mugwump (mug on one side, wump on<br>
the other) on the issue of ordained lady ministers.  I've read some material<br>
which was not in favor and the writers seemed to have done a good job<br>
of marshalling Scripture, SoP quotes, and their own verbiage, in a clear,<br>
coherent manner, to support their position.  I trust, then, that those<br>
favoring it in the SDA church have prepared cogent, non-acrimonious position<br>
papers (or whatever) which delineate those Scripture verses and SoP<br>
quotations which they believe support their position.<br>
<p>
Could one of you kindly post an "executive briefing" type article to<br>
SDAnet and perhaps suggest some further reading so that I can understand.<br>
<p>
You see, the only thing that counts is whether or not it is in God's will<br>
(John 5:19,30).  If we're out of His will on this, we could get a big<br>
surprise (cf Acts 9:5).<br>
<pre>
