Edgar Vega writes<br>
	Ruben :<br>
<p>
	The SDA church grew a lot (in knowledge and number) when people were<br>
	worried about knowing better the Scriptures rather than who is at the<br>
	pulpit or what gender does mi pastor belongs to?  The SDA church in USA<br>
	is not growing as much as before because our priorities have changed.<br>
	Remember the church is just what we are.<br>
	Edgar<br>
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -<br>
I write<br>
<p>
	Your message seems to say that speaking out on issues that aren't pronounced<br>
as the word "salvation", is changing our priorities, and ultimately the <br>
churches.  To a point<br>
this is true.  However, your tone of "voice" (if there can be one in <br>
netland) - - by phrases like,<br>
"knowing better the scriptures 'rather than' who is at the pulpit" - - <br>
gives the impression that<br>
attention to such things as discrimination in the treatment of women <br>
theologians, is a bad<br>
thing.  To this I must disagree.<br>
	Who on SDAnet has read the Desire of Ages?  I'm glad one religion teacher at<br>
WWC, Bud Roberts, had us read it, for his Life and Teachings of Jesus <br>
(LTJ) class.<br>
I tell you, my life has never been the same, and anytime I return <br>
there, I'm always renewed.<br>
If you haven't, please read it, and if you have, I promise that it <br>
won't harm you to read it again.<br>
To skip to the study of Daniel and Revelation, or the Great Controversy <br>
without keeping our<br>
hearts fixed on Jesus's life and teachings, we do our souls a GREAT <br>
disservice.  We are<br>
back to building communities of religious thought without the CORNERSTONE..<br>
Jesus is the one in the saving business, and we are only the <br>
messengers, inviting others.<br>
It is too easy for us to try and put Gods ability to work in a test <br>
tube, and only allow God to<br>
work in that confined area.  For God to work in a slightly different <br>
way or to use a different<br>
tool (which we are) is to spring a surprise on us - - "God, we forgot <br>
to tell you, 'we don't like<br>
surprises'."<br>
	I believe STRONGLY that the people who keep all of the commandments of<br>
God and the testimony of *Jesus*, will be the remnant, the end of the <br>
line of Christians...<br>
Christ copy-cats.  The time will come when there won't be anymore <br>
Adventist seminaries,<br>
won't it be nice to say, "before they chained our doors shut, we <br>
overcame prejudice."<br>
THIS MESSAGE IS ESPECIALLY FOR MARCUS STRINGER, THE *CHIEF* OF SINNERS.<br>
