<title>Feb_1993: Licensed Ministers</title>
<h1>Licensed Ministers</h1>
Warren C Trenchard (<i>70711.3366@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>21 Feb 93 20:42:00 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#214">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#214">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#214">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#214">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0215.html">Lisa Parry: "Re: Thinking big"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0213.html">Allyn Craig: "Re: Michael Card Songs"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the North American Division, licensed ministers may perform all the<br>
duties of an ordained minister.  However, their performance of such<br>
duties is limited to those churches in which they are ordained as local<br>
elders.  Any exceptions to this are to be approved by the local<br>
conference administration.<br>
<p>
Warren C. Trenchard<br>
Internet: 70711.3366@compuserve.com<br>
CIS: 70711,3366<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0215.html">Lisa Parry: "Re: Thinking big"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0213.html">Allyn Craig: "Re: Michael Card Songs"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
