Problem 4: Not enough houses in our Chicago sized town to cover<br>
the anxious members who want to go visiting to look for interested<br>
non-members.  Having to drive long distances to find people who<br>
haven't been visited.<br>
<p>
Problem 5: Overzealous youth group - wants to get involved in<br>
church outreach ministry all the time, and due to aforementioned<br>
problems, the ministry group is already bursting at the seams.<br>
<p>
Problem 6: Elderly over-cared for - They enjoy the visits, food,<br>
and help given to them by church members, but are unable to<br>
eat all of the food or find work for the eager helpers.<br>
<p>
Problem 7: Too many mission minded people - can't find overseas<br>
calls for all that want to go, even using student missions<br>
jobs.<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"If God is for us, who can be against us?"            Lisa Parry
