<title>Feb_1993: OT Laws -- Applicability</title>
<h1>OT Laws -- Applicability</h1>
Tim Swensen (<i>swensen@ecn.purdue.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 18 Feb 93 21:57:14 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#219">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#219">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#219">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#219">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0220.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Re: The "Sharing Scripture" SS lesson"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0218.html">Steven Timm: "The "Sharing Scripture" SS lesson"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0231.html">Woody Baker: "Re: OT Laws -- Applicability"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
Here are some questions I have pondered at some length.  Would any of you<br>
be willing and able to point me to some answers?<br>
<p>
Old Testament Laws -- Their Applicability Today<br>
-----------------------------------------------<br>
1.  Of the many laws given in Exodus, Leviticus, etc... what principles do<br>
    we use to determine which are applicable today?<br>
<p>
2.  Are the specific laws important today, or just their underlying principles?<br>
<p>
3.  Elaborating on #1, SDAs still hold that the food laws are binding, the <br>
    reason being that they apply to health and are therefore not abolished with<br>
    the sacrificial system.  How about such laws as not were garments made from<br>
    more than one type of fabric?  How about various "camp" laws governing<br>
    infectious disease (skin diseases and the like)?  How about purity laws<br>
    (mensturating women going outside the camp)?<br>
<p>
I am searching for Biblical principles of interpretation here.  Adventists <br>
(rightly, I believe) have pointed to the Ten Commandments as have special<br>
significance (written with God's own finger).  But what about the others?<br>
Paul vigorously disposed of circumcision.  Is our basis for ignoring many<br>
of the Levitical laws the same basis Paul used to do away with circumcision?<br>
<p>
I have a theory covering some of these laws, but would like some help here.<br>
Any takers?<br>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
swensen@ecn.purdue.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
