In the 1991 Congressional Staff Directory Rep Bob Stump lists Seventh-day<br>
Adventist as his religion. Rep. Stump has served since Jan. 3, 1977. He<br>
lists his profession as "farmer" and his home as Tolleson, Arizona.<br>
<p>
He is Republican and serves on the Committee on Armed Services and  the<br>
Committee on Veterans' Affairs as the Ranking Minority Member.<br>
<p>
This is not surprising since he served in the U.S. Navy from 1943-1946.<br>
<p>
Incidentally, I first discovered Rep. Stump while watching C-SPANN.<br>
They listed the church affiliations and number of members with that<br>
affiliation one day. I noticed one SDA and determined to find out who it<br>
was. That took me to the 1991 Congressional Staff Directory. <br>
<p>
Pam Harris<br>
