<!-- body="start" -->
What I meant by "food laws" was any law referring to what can and cannot<br>
be eaten. The way I understand it, SDAs believe that the ceremonial law<br>
system *as law* no longer stands. This seems to be supported by the<br>
quotation from "SDAs believe" posted by Drew(?).<br>
<p>
This is not to say that SDAs disregard Biblical advice as to what should<br>
and should not be eaten. We see the Eden diet as the ideal, with the<br>
post-flood omnivorous diet as second best.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
