One should note beside the other things mentioned so far about ROmans<br>
6:14, that there appears to be in Romans an equivalence between being<br>
under the law and being sold to sin.  FOr THis can be seen in Rom. 6 when<br>
he is talking about being a slave to sin.  It is even in verse 14.  FOr<br>
Paul sin used the law to bring a death sentence upon him.  THis comes out<br>
in the interesting personification of sin in Rom. 7.  SOme other Pauline<br>
insights I have come across lately are :  IN RROm. 12 one has some<br>
parallels to Jesus' sermon on the mount.  In Galations there are some<br>
parallels to Hebrews -- Gal. 4:22-31 and hHebrews 12:18-29. <br>
Ian.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
