<title>Nov_1992: Re: God's love</title>
<h1>Re: God's love</h1>
Bill Oblitey (<i>OBLITEY@grove.iup.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 11 Nov 1992 11:32 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#21">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#21">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#21">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#21">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0022.html">Bill Oblitey: "Re: Earvin "Magic" Johnson"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0020.html">David Plaisted: "God's love"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0020.html">David Plaisted: "God's love"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;SDAnet,</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;One of my teachers at the university said that she doesn't accept</i><br>
<i>&gt;Christian believes because she can't understand how God could be</i><br>
<i>&gt;love if He demands a sacrifice (see John 3:16).  She finds the idea</i><br>
<i>&gt;that Jesus on the cross would manifest God's love incomprehesible.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;What would you say to this educated woman who does believe in supernatural,</i><br>
<i>&gt;in some "greater power" or "universal love" but not in "our" God ??</i><br>
<i>&gt;I wasn't able to give her a good answer and I'd really like to know </i><br>
<i>&gt;what you would have said!</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;				Minna</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
Minna,<br>
Let me give this a try:<br>
If God's love does not accept sacrifices, <br>
   then God must accept sin.<br>
If God accepts sin,<br>
   then Satan must rule,<br>
  because his accusation of God's love cannot be refuted<br>
  and Adam, me, and everyone else must live in sin - which God condones.<br>
<p>
It is because of His love that we have sacrifice (I'm in trouble already).<br>
Furthermore, it's because of His love that the sacrifice was not you, me, your<br>
professor, Adam, or even an angel in heaven but His own beloved Son.<br>
He would not hold back anything to redeem us.<br>
<p>
If God accepts sin, then He must cease to exist and Satan will have to assume<br>
rulership of God's universe or all of us must accept chaos.<br>
<p>
Bill Oblitey<br>
[OBLITEY@OAK.GROVE.IUP.EDU]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
