Magic Johnson was baptized as a boy by Dr. Leslie Anderson who was then pastor<br>
in Michigan and currently serving as the Health/Temperance and Inner City <br>
Director for the Northern California Conference. His family were charter <br>
members of the church that was formed after a crusade. His mother and sisters <br>
are still active members in that church. Dr. Anderson met with Magic a few <br>
months back in Sacramento, CA to appeal to him to return to the religion of <br>
his youth. Two Elders from the Roseville Church near Sacramento also met with <br>
Johnson. This information comes from a personal conversation with Dr. Anderson<br>
and the pastor of the Roseville church. Both are personal friends of mine.<br>
<p>
Ed Fargusson (Compuserve 72450,2430)<br>
