I will start compiling the digest of SDAnet messages this week.  Messages<br>
starting today and going to the following Sunday will be in the first<br>
issue.  This is primarily concerned with Compuserve readers who are <br>
paying a per-message charge.  A few people have expressed a tentative <br>
interest.  However no one will receive this digest unless they explicitly<br>
request to do so.<br>
<p>
Warning, it won't be pretty.  It will be 30-50 messages stuck from end to end.<br>
<p>
If you want to receive this digest instead of the regular SDAnet, please<br>
send mail explicitly to me.  This is ideal for the person who only reads<br>
about once a week anyway.  By reducing traffic of 100-200 messages to four,<br>
I hope we can alleviate the cost concerns of our Compuserve readers.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
