<title>Nov_1992: Halloween</title>
<h1>Halloween</h1>
Pam Harris (<i>HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU</i>)<br>
<i>02 Nov 1992 22:45:07 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#8">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#8">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#8">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#8">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0009.html">Raylene: "Re: Halloween"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0007.html">Ruben Munoz-Larrondo: "AVONDALE COLLEGE"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0009.html">Raylene: "Re: Halloween"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
As a child we did NOT celebrate Halloween. It was a purely innocent time<br>
to have a costume party, to go trick-or-treating or Pathfinder food gathering,<br>
and to have a fall festival bob-for-apples type church social.<br>
<p>
In no way was it "celebrated" or the Satanic rituals recognized. Just because<br>
the Devil has corrupted the celebration of the recognition of Christ's<br>
birth and his show of power as resurrected Saviour (wouldn't we expect him<br>
to make negative the positive), does not mean that one is worldly or<br>
Satanic or pagan to recognize the religious holidays and celebrate<br>
them. These are some of the most wonderful family times in our culture<br>
and fond adult memories of "family" trace to the innocent celebration<br>
of these events.<br>
<p>
The sack of candy that we managed to collect was strictly doled out over<br>
a period of months by my mother who never allowed us to gorge. So the<br>
delight of that childhood time stretched till Thanksgiving, the next<br>
special family time. <br>
<p>
With all the darkness and unhappiness and sorrow in this life, it is a<br>
shame we must single out carefully celebrated holidays for criticism<br>
and divisiveness. With all due respect to anyone who does not wish to<br>
observe these holidays, please be tolerant with those who make these times<br>
spiritual, family and other-centered, times of fellowship and giving.<br>
We can major in minors and die of stress-related disease. Life is too<br>
short to get bogged down in some of these petty issues. I've never<br>
known an Adventist yet who uplifted Satanic rituals and dressed their<br>
children in witches costumes. My predominently Adventist neighborhood<br>
is sought after by parents with young children at Halloween time because<br>
they know they can trust this neighborhood's treats as safe. I guess<br>
I've said my piece.<br>
<p>
Pam Harris<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
