<title>Nov_1992: For better or worse, election almost over</title>
<h1>For better or worse, election almost over</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue,  3 Nov 1992 09:43:09 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#10">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#10">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#10">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#10">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0011.html">Tony: "Re: For better or worse, election almost over"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0009.html">Raylene: "Re: Halloween"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0011.html">Tony: "Re: For better or worse, election almost over"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The US Presidential campaign will be over in a few hours, and it will <br>
be a few hours more before the 1996 campaign starts.  The moderator<br>
decided to let me post my personal view of the election after all.<br>
I voted for Bill Clinton based on concerns of religious liberty, health<br>
care, the economy, racial harmony and his support for the kind of big<br>
science spending which currently provides me with a job.<br>
<p>
No matter who wins the election, I'm sure SDA conspiracy theorists will <br>
find a way to predict that the time of trouble is at hand during the <br>
upcoming administration.  Sooner or later, one of these times they will <br>
be right.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
