Thx for voting your conscience.  As a Canadian living in the US (hence<br>
not getting to vote anywhere about anything) I've felt a dilemma (if I<br>
had been voting in the US).  I appreciate some of George Bush's stands<br>
(e.g., pro-life, but I'm doubtful if he does that from conscience; I<br>
suspect expediency) while concerned about others.  Same pos/neg tho'ts re<br>
Clinton.  Seemed to me that Perot grasped a lot of the monetary issues<br>
(deficit) but I think his protectionism has some problems, let alone concerns<br>
that he thinks you can run government (consensus) like a business<br>
(top-down autocracy in many ways).<br>
