<title>Nov_1992: Madalyn - Again?</title>
<h1>Madalyn - Again?</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 6 Nov 92 15:06:11 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#15">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#15">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#15">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#15">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0016.html">Cam Litvin: "Earvin "Magic" Johnson"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0014.html">Paul Gates: "GC/NAD FAX"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Last Sabbath, in all seriousness, our church's Religious Liberty person<br>
got up and announced that Madalyn Murray O"Hair, the lady who got the<br>
Supreme Court to kick the Bible out of schools in the 60's, was meeting with<br>
the FCC on Nov 10 to get them to remove religious programming from radio.<br>
He then waved several photocopied sheets in the air and suggested we<br>
get a copy, sign the protest, and send it to the FCC.<br>
<p>
I got the impression that our pastor was not surprised (usually he's<br>
pretty with it) so I assume the RL person mentioned he was going to<br>
talk about this.  Anyway, I raised my hand and asked, "How is this<br>
time different from past times which proved to be rumors and false?"<br>
The RL person looked at me blankly and said, "I don't know."<br>
<p>
Unless my memory is failing me, the various union/conference papers and<br>
even the Review (let alone Dear Abby and Ann Landers) have printed stories<br>
indicating that these Madalyn/FCC rumors continue to circulate (how many<br>
years now?) despite attempts to eradicate them.<br>
<p>
Me oh my.  Well, so that I don't become like the boy who cried "Wolf!",<br>
anyone one out there in Rumor Control land know if this is rumor (as I<br>
suspect) or true (finally 8-().<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
