Steve, I saw this earlier today.  I'll leave it to your judgment<br>
whether it should be posted or not.  It is not my intention that<br>
SDAnet should be a gossip column.  But considering Magic's influence<br>
I thought it very interesting that he disclosed this.<br>
<p>
<p>
This morning (Nov 9) on "The Today Show" Magic Johnson said his mother was/is<br>
a Seventh-Day Adventist.  I had heard rumors of this several years ago<br>
but had never had it substantiated, until I heard him say it.  He also<br>
said something about when he was looking for a college to go to, his<br>
family took into consideration when the school played it games, prefer-<br>
ably not on Friday Evenings and Saturday afternoons.  Unfortunatly, I<br>
did not hear much more as I had to leave for work.<br>
<p>
--Cam Litvin  PROFS Support  CLLITVIN<br>
<p>
<p>
[This was quite well-known in Michigan when I was growing up.  Various<br>
people at my academy were from Lansing and said they had played basketball<br>
with his brothers and sisters.  I believe some other of his brothers and <br>
sisters also belong to the church.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
