<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
One of my teachers at the university said that she doesn't accept<br>
Christian believes because she can't understand how God could be<br>
love if He demands a sacrifice (see John 3:16).  She finds the idea<br>
that Jesus on the cross would manifest God's love incomprehesible.<br>
<p>
What would you say to this educated woman who does believe in supernatural,<br>
in some "greater power" or "universal love" but not in "our" God ??<br>
I wasn't able to give her a good answer and I'd really like to know <br>
what you would have said!<br>
<p>
				Minna<br>
 <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
