<title>Nov_1992: Re:  Halloween or Reformation Day?</title>
<h1>Re:  Halloween or Reformation Day?</h1>
Dan Blake (<i>dblake@hprnd.rose.hp.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 10 Nov 92 12:44:26 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#19">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#19">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#19">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#19">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0020.html">David Plaisted: "God's love"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0018.html">Malachi Robertson: "Madalyn - Again?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Fred Christiansen writes]<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; When we had children we determined to find a Godly focus for this time</i><br>
<i>&gt; of year.  What we found was:  Oct 31 was the day Martin Luther nailed</i><br>
<i>&gt; his 95 Theses to the door of the church in Wittenburg.  Some Protestants</i><br>
<i>&gt; refer to this as Reformation Day.  We have found this to be far preferable.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
Thanks for the reminder Fred.  I'm surprised I let Reformation Day slip<br>
by us this year.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; The night before, he [Frederick the Wise] had a "continued story" series of</i><br>
<i>&gt; three dreams.  In them a monk, writings on the door of Wittenburg's church,</i><br>
<i>&gt; the Pope's tiara, a large pen reaching to Rome, and the Elector figured</i><br>
<i>&gt; prominently.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Oh, yes, in the dream, Frederick asked the monk whence came the large pen.</i><br>
<i>&gt; The monk answered, "From a goose in Bohemia."  Bonus points if you know</i><br>
<i>&gt; who the goose was and why the symbolism was apt.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
I'm not sure of the symbolism, but might the goose in Bohemia<br>
be Jan Hus (John Huss)?  He preceded Frederick and Luther by<br>
about 100 years but was certainly a precursor to the Reformation.<br>
Hus was a martyr (burned as a heretic) for the cause of Christ in<br>
1415.<br>
<p>
Dan Blake<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
