<!-- body="start" -->
Hmmm, I've never thought about it outside of it just being a "thing".<br>
The identity of the individual who's feet we wash doesn't seem critical<br>
for salvation.  Ideally, it would change every time.  Let married people<br>
wash each other's feet, let friends, let strangers.  The focus should be<br>
in humbling ourselves to be servants to our spouses, children, elders<br>
strangers, and yes, even our enemies.<br>
<p>
Glad you asked the question though.  It made me thing.<br>
<p>
MarcusS<br>
