<p>
I attended (was paid to sing at) the Maundy Thursday (beginning of Easter<br>
weekend) service at a nearby Catholic church this past spring.  I gathered<br>
that it is the tradition at such services for the officiating priest to<br>
wash the feet of 12 men (no women or children) representative of the<br>
congregation.<br>
