Steven Timm writes:<br>
<p>
[ among lots of other things ]<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;whatever that may be.  ("Adventism" itself is a word I would like to </i><br>
<i>&gt;excise from the language.  We do not refer to the religion of Baptists</i><br>
<i>&gt;as "Baptism", do we?)  </i><br>
<p>
Maybe not, but it does refer to one of their beliefs/practices just as<br>
adventism refers to one of ours.  <br>
<p>
Also, we have Catholicism, Anglicanism, Episcopalianism, Methodism, and<br>
even Atheism and Paganism.  So I don't think the word can be ruled out<br>
on purely etymological grounds.<br>
<p>
I assume that Steve's point is that, at least in current usage,<br>
adventism != Adventism.  You choose which you wish to be (either, both,<br>
or, if it pleases you, neither).<br>
