(To the SDA Net)<br>
Good evening Steve,<br>
<p>
I down loaded your first SDA NET digest and just finished reading it.<br>
There seemed to be quite a few comments on feet washing/Communion Service.<br>
<p>
I see no problem with spouses washing each other's feet as a part of the<br>
communion service. I suppose there could be a problem with singles not<br>
liking the idea but wherever I participated in this type of a service<br>
there was also provision for women/women and men/men.<br>
<p>
On the Sabbath's that we conduct the service I speak for only 10-15<br>
minutes and before we separate for the feet/washing part I instruct the<br>
congregation about the service, etc. no secular talking and recommend that<br>
the person have a prayer for the one they are serving. No one mentioned it<br>
but as Adventists we believe in open communion which simply means<br>
christians of any faith may join in with us if they so desire.<br>
<p>
After church on that Sabbath of Communion, the elders and I decide who<br>
will take communion to members that were absent that day.<br>
<p>
On another subject: I agree that just because the Bible is silent on an<br>
issue, that is no criteria for support or non-support. If we wanted to<br>
make something out of that, it would seem to indicate that it was not a<br>
problem in Bible times.<br>
<p>
Does anyone know anything about this organization in Angwin, CA that puts<br>
out these video tapes. I have seen some of the tapes and it seems to<br>
"smack" of Hartland Institute which as you all know is located in Va. This<br>
organization calls themselves LL? productions or some similar thing like<br>
that.<br>
<p>
Since I voted for Clinton, I was pleased that he won the election. I could<br>
be wrong but I think we are going to see some good things happen with the<br>
new administration.<br>
<p>
That's all for now.<br>
<p>
...........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
