Recently I was asked to answer a question on the symbolism of footwashing--<br>
was it a mini-baptism or a symbol of humility.  I found the material in<br>
the chapter "Servant of Servants" in Desire of Ages to be most illuminating.<br>
<p>
I think we as individuals have the chance to foster change.  We may not change<br>
everyone, but my partner and I can talk of the right things, pray together, and<br>
enjoy the blessings of footwashing.  Perhaps others may copy what they see.<br>
<p>
Let change start with me!!<br>
<p>
Nancy<br>
