GO 92 is to be held at Andrews University from December 27 to 31.  It is <br>
billed as an International Young Adult Missions Conference.  There will<br>
be plenary speakers, small groups, seminars, etc.  <br>
<p>
Featured speakers are Tony Campolo, Dick Barron --Student missionary leader,<br>
Eugene Hsu--in charge of work in China, Mike Ryan--head of Global Mission,<br>
Ted Wick--I'm not sure, Pat Gustin--former lady missionary to Thailand, <br>
currently at Walla Walla College, John Kent, and Borge Schantz, of the<br>
Centre for Islamic Studies at Newbold College, England.  <br>
<p>
Two main tracks in morning meetings:  Mission explorers or How to adopt a<br>
People group.<br>
<p>
More than 20 exhibitors.<br>
<p>
Price: Everything included--food, lodging, seminars = $65 before Dec. 1<br>
						      $75 after Dec. 1<br>
       No food, no lodging                          = $40 before Dec. 1<br>
						      $50 after Dec. 1<br>
<p>
Contact Institute of World Mission, Sutherland House University,<br>
Berrien Springs, MI 49104.  616 471 2521.<br>
