The words of "Malachi Robertson"  (Ian R. Brown)<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I guess one of the important rules that I hold in Bible study is the rule</i><br>
<i>&gt; of checking out the context.  A lot of times I find this is not done, but</i><br>
<i>&gt; instead a passage is taken out of context.  Now by context I mean the word</i><br>
<i>&gt; in a broad sense:  there is the immediate writen context of the passage</i><br>
<i>&gt; with the verses near the  verses in question and of the BIble as a whole;</i><br>
<i>&gt; there is also historical context ; and one I guess might also include</i><br>
<i>&gt; language context, that is what did certain words mean and how were they</i><br>
<i>&gt; used.  After one has down the meaning of one passage or weveral passages,,</i><br>
<i>&gt; Tthen I supppose comes what I call the 'So What?' rule, where one must ask</i><br>
<i>&gt; how the meaning of these passages impacts our life or at least applies to</i><br>
<i>&gt; our life.  I guess maybe the last rule may not always be applicacable.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Ian.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
