<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;I think many people would be better off simply practicing</i><br>
<i>&gt;nuts-and-bolts Christianity and staying completely out of theology.</i><br>
<i>&gt;Glen McCluskey</i><br>
<p>
That may be so but isn't that precisely what the Catholic Church <br>
attempted in the dark ages? The result: the Church is not kept accountable.<br>
<p>
It is also the beauty of the SDA church, that the individual is considered <br>
intelligent enough to explore the Bible for themselves. The remarkable thing <br>
is that, in the first place, our beliefs were not developed by especially <br>
educated people.<br>
<p>
Raylene<br>
---*---<br>
