To Steve Timm &amp; the Net:<br>
<p>
I was just wondering if any of the "Hams" on the net are on Packet Radio?<br>
A "Node" was just put on the air about 3 blocks from my house so it is<br>
very easy to access it with a 2 meter handitalkie with no outdoor<br>
antenna. Of course one of the advantages is that you can access ham radio<br>
BBSs and it is FREE! Ah yes!! Well I guess that is not exactly true!! You<br>
need an amateur license, 2 meter radio, data controller, and a computer.<br>
<p>
I noticed that in Cheryl's message that she had forgotten my call. I do<br>
not feel bad about that because I have had a rough time remembering her<br>
call!! But, Cheryl, I have a system now. I just think of X hertz.<br>
<p>
I apologize for boring the "other" net members on the net who are not<br>
hams.<br>
<p>
.........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
