I am sorry it has taken so long to reply to some of the feedback on the idea <br>
of a Seventh-day Adventist forum on Compuserve. I have just moved and it has <br>
taken a while to get settled.<br>
<p>
I think I didn't explain what a forum would be like for those who are not <br>
familiar with Compuserve. One section would be for messages much like SDAnet. <br>
I don't see this replacing SDAnet at all. The audience would be much different<br>
and I don't think it would have the same interest.<br>
<p>
The main purpose of a forum would be to have access to the Union Papers and <br>
all articles on line. Also other files could be available including templates <br>
for membership databases or finance software for churches. Another possible <br>
use would be uploading graphics that might be of particular interest to SDAs <br>
(i.e. Image of Daniel 2, etc.) It could grow to the point where other services<br>
would be available on line.<br>
<p>
It would be my desire to see SDAnet continue the important dialogues which <br>
occur now. A Compuserve forum would serve another purpose.<br>
<p>
A note on Compuserve E-Mail. It depends on which options you have as to what <br>
the charges are for E-Mail. Personally my volume is usually low enough that I <br>
pay nothing for receiving SDAnet. Occasionally traffic is high enough that I <br>
have a small surcharge. It is a small price to pay for the benefits received.<br>
With Compuserve Information Manager, the software I use, I can also see what <br>
is the subject of a message before downloading it. I can then decide if it is <br>
of value to me and choose to download it or delete it. There is no charge for <br>
the message if I delete it from my mail box before downloading it.<br>
<p>
I hope this helps clarify a few things.<br>
<p>
Ed Fargusson (Compuserve 72450,2430)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
