<title>Nov_1992: Joe and his bathroom rituals</title>
<h1>Joe and his bathroom rituals</h1>
cheryl berthelsen (<i>cherylb@csd4.csd.uwm.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 27 Nov 92 00:22:05 -0600</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#84">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#84">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#84">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#84">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0085.html">TANG BENG YONG: "S.O.P. texts"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0083.html">David Plaisted: "principles of interpretation"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The fact that parents may be concerned about their children should NOT be<br>
a reason to ban Joe from coming to church.  In fact, I think it would be<br>
an excellent opportunity to teach the children at your church about people<br>
who are different, about how to have a healthy cautiousness towards<br>
strangers without evoking fear.  It also may have a positive effect in<br>
keeping the kids from lingering and playing around in the bathroom.  My<br>
own experience with kids and church has been that many times kids ask to<br>
go to the bathroom from their classes merely to "escape" Sabbath School or<br>
church.  If bathroom use was limited to between services where plenty of<br>
adult supervision would be available there should be nothing to fear about<br>
Joe in the bathroom.<br>
<p>
The time following church and during the potluck might be a bit more difficult<br>
but I still think that it shouldn't be a problem if kids are taught to go<br>
to the restroom with at least one friend.  In fact, this is very good habit<br>
to develop no matter where a child is.<br>
<p>
If the church members are seriously concerned about Joe, someone on the<br>
board might contact the local police and see if Joes has any kind of<br>
record of complaints against him.  The lack of such a record could be<br>
used to alleviate the concerns some might have.  Then reach out the this<br>
hurting man in a Christian manner and don't push him away.  Jesus certainly<br>
would not behave this way.  Remember that church exists for everyone, not<br>
the elite of this world who don't seem to have problems.<br>
<p>
Cheryl<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
