<!-- body="start" -->
Hi Steve,<br>
	I have a friend who bought the Ellen White CD and runs it on his<br>
CD ROM. He wrote a Wordperfect macro to edit texts from it into continuous<br>
text files. Using that, he can get any article from her writings in a text<br>
file. If you want any E. G. White writings as a text file, I can send it<br>
to you. I have Steps to Christ, Thoughts from the Mt. of Blessing, GC chapters<br>
32 to the end, the 1st 9 chapters of PP, texts about the nature of Christ,<br>
prayer, planning for public evengelism, and other stuff.<br>
	- Beng Tang, National University of Singapore.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
