<title>May_1992: Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works</title>
<h1>Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works</h1>
Victor Ortiz (<i>ortiz@susan.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 29 Apr 92 10:15:35 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#0">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#0">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#0">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#0">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0001.html">Fred Christiansen: "Paul Harvey on diet and Ellen White"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; # A non-SDA friend of mine that I see frequently.  He ended up wanting to</i><br>
<i>&gt; # talk about tithing.  He said that his not tithing used to bother him</i><br>
<i>&gt; # enormously but he thanks God that He has delivered him from that</i><br>
<i>&gt; # affliction so that he can now go about with a free conscience over it.</i><br>
<i>&gt; # He anticipates that in His own good time God will make the way possible</i><br>
<i>&gt; # and show him when and how to go about tithing.  "Its in the Lord's</i><br>
<i>&gt; # hands now and so I don't worry about it anymore."</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; And people wonder why they don't see God moving in their lives!!</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; My take on tithing is pretty simple.  God owns it all.  Ten percent is</i><br>
<i>&gt; the starting point in my giving.  God has given me a job and an</i><br>
<i>&gt; income.  Every penny belongs to Him.  And I recall that when it comes</i><br>
<i>&gt; time to write the check.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
 I also have a pretty simple view on tithing.  It is very clear in the Bible    that God wants us to tithe.  It is also very clear that if we do not tithe we   are stealing from God.  And we all now that to steal is to break one of the ten commandments.  It is probably all the worse when we steal from God.   <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
