<title>May_1992: Paul Harvey on diet and Ellen White</title>
<h1>Paul Harvey on diet and Ellen White</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 29 Apr 92 8:57:18 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#1">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#1">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#1">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#1">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0002.html">Jeff Tosk: "Re: Leadership of SDA-L in transition"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0000.html">Victor Ortiz: "Re: Let me see if I have this correct on saved by works"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
This morning's short-form Paul Harvey news included mention of the<br>
new dietary recommendations of the US gov't.  He chuckled and said<br>
they are finally catching up with what Ellen White said 100 years ago.<br>
Might be interesting to catch his long-form noon news and see if<br>
he expands any on that.<br>
<p>
Also, recently, he recommended Vandeman's "Cry of the Lonely Planet."<br>
Evidently he keeps some track of things in the SDA church.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola TSD (DW278), 2900 S. Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ  85282
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  For the Lord gives wisdom:  out of His mouth comes knowledge
    and understanding (Prov 2:6).
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
