<title>May_1992: Leadership of SDA-L in transition</title>
<h1>Leadership of SDA-L in transition</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+%ANDREW.CMU.EDU%CMU.EDU@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 29 Apr 1992 21:00:05 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#3">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#3">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#3">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#3">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0004.html">Eric Snyder: "dietary info"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0002.html">Jeff Tosk: "Re: Leadership of SDA-L in transition"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Christine Hwang has asked me to take over her function as keeper of<br>
the SDA-L membership list, which I have agreed to do.<br>
We are still working out the technical details.  There will be<br>
an update in a couple days.  However, no immediate changes to the<br>
format of either SDA-L or SDAnet are in order.<br>
 <br>
I know the work at Enoch's end of the thing handling all the technical<br>
details is even more time-consuming than Christine's end of it.<br>
Certainly it would help if we could add another co-listowner who is<br>
actually at LLUVM.  There are other people who have also volunteered to<br>
help, and I will be contacting them soon.<br>
 <br>
Enoch and Christine haven't got anywhere near the credit they deserve<br>
for making the capacity of a LISTSERV available to us.  LLUVM is<br>
the only VM node in the Adventist system, to my knowledge, and it's<br>
a resource I don't take lightly.  Netland owes a debt of gratitude to<br>
their management for making this available, and we want to see it continue.<br>
 <br>
Once all the technical details are worked out, we'll post a status report<br>
and then begin a discussion of what SDA-L should be.<br>
 <br>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
