<!-- body="start" -->
  I just opened my Bible looking for something totally different and my<br>
attention was caught by the word Presbytery in the index.  After reading<br>
about presbytery in 1 Tim 4:14 I started reading from v1.  Paul is<br>
telling the people about what will happen in the 'latter times'.<br>
<p>
  I leave it to the reader of this note to check out 1 Tim 4 for<br>
themselves.<br>
<p>
  Paul says that animal flesh was good, from God, intended for our<br>
eating, and that all animals fall into this category.  In fact, he talks<br>
quite strongly against those who would do the things listed in verse 3.<br>
<p>
  As I understand it you don't forbid the eating of meat, just say that<br>
the original diet of Adam and Eve is better (can't argue with that, why,<br>
even modern science is catching on to that).<br>
<p>
Scott       | No success can compensate for failure in the home. David O. McKay<br>
Mattes      | President 1951-70, Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints<br>
