<!-- body="start" -->
In discussions with Enoch Hwang in the past week, we have come to the<br>
following agreement:<br>
 <br>
Enoch Hwang will stay with SDA-L and keep the same responsibilities he<br>
has always had with the list, namely being in charge of the technical<br>
details at LLUVM, as well as being the first and deciding list-owner.<br>
The list may move nodes this summer as La Sierra gets its own Internet<br>
connection.<br>
 <br>
I (Steve Timm) will be added to the list as a list-owner.  For the time<br>
being I will maintain the directory of list members, although in time<br>
I'd be willing to have helpers in this task.  We are still working on<br>
the technical details of what it will take to add me as a listowner, so<br>
please hold off all subscriber requests for a little while longer while<br>
we are working this out.  We are exploring ways to give better service<br>
on SET NOMAIL commands as well as subscribing and desubscribing.<br>
When these are worked out, I'll post another message to the net.<br>
 <br>
Part of the hassle for the listowners of SDA-L to date has been lots of<br>
people that move away and don't desubscribe from the list.  I see a lot<br>
of people that I know from SDAnet are long gone from addresses, still<br>
current on the SDA-L list.  Mail to these people bounces and goes to the<br>
listowners.<br>
 <br>
The SDA-L membership list has historically been public, in fact, anyone<br>
across the country can REVIEW SDA-L and get it.  It's possible to hide<br>
yourself from this review if you wish.  I will send details once we get it<br>
worked out.  The SDAnet membership list has been posted a couple times<br>
before, but any members who don't want their name posted as part of the<br>
membership directory should let me know and I will leave it out.<br>
The new edition of the membership directory will come out shortly.<br>
 <br>
More details to follow, and once again we want to thank Christine for<br>
her service to SDA-L in the past year and a half, and congratulate her<br>
on the upcoming completion of her degree.<br>
 <br>
Steve Timm<br>
