<!-- body="start" -->
I think some clarification on the SDA position on diet is in order.<br>
To my knowledge, I don't think any SDA's claim that the Bible<br>
enjoins vegetarianism on all.  The official church position is that <br>
we are allowed to eat clean meats only.  So Nancy Vyhmeister's analysis<br>
of the warning against people who forbid the eating of certain meats was<br>
designed to show that it is not directed against us per se.  In this <br>
analysis I agree with her.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
