<!-- body="start" -->
I believe that the listserv has a built-in facility for such an<br>
occurrence.  If said user does not post within a certain length of time,<br>
the listserv would send email to the user telling him/her to confirm<br>
their membership by sending a CONFIRM SDA-L command to LISTSERV, and<br>
giving the user a week or so to do so.  If the user fails to send the<br>
command, then (s)he will be automatically unsubscribed from the list.<br>
Just thought I'd bring this up for the list owners so that they may<br>
utilize this feature and get less bounced mail.<br>
 <br>
Jerome Grimmer<br>
ST6267@SIUCVMB.BITNET, ST6267@SIUCVMB.siu.edu<br>
