To Scott Mattes:<br>
<p>
Scott I believe you have "works" in correct perspective. A "red-blooded"<br>
Adventist (Grin!!) in fact I should say "any" instead of "A", will agree<br>
with you. Where the "rub" comes is when a person focuses on "works'<br>
entirely when our focus should be on Jesus Christ. I am sure that some on<br>
this SDA net will disagree but........ I come back to the premise that I<br>
have said before, we are saved by faith and faith only, but that faith if<br>
it is true faith will produce a "life of obedience." You know what cheap<br>
grace is which is the idea once you accept Christ you no longer have to<br>
have good works you can do any old thing which is not true.<br>
<p>
The other faction is just as bad if not worse in Adventism when people<br>
think that people can only be talking about cheap grace when they talk<br>
about accepting Christ by faith. There is a difference.<br>
<p>
Paul<br>
