<title>May_1992: Freedoms in the USA</title>
<h1>Freedoms in the USA</h1>
Dave Buxton (<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 13 May 92 08:34:52 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#23">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#23">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#23">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#23">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0024.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: 1 Tim 4"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0022.html">Steven Timm: "New SDA-L / SDAnet directory"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
A few weeks ago there were those protesting how the drug laws were<br>
infringing on freedoms.  People having their cash taken away because<br>
they bought their airline tickets with cash - the drug cops assuming<br>
that anyone in an airport with a large sum of cash was out to make<br>
a drug deal.  Cars, learjets, etc found guilty of having drugs aboard.<br>
For example a charter flight company looses his learjet because his<br>
passenger was carrying drugs and the drug dealer was anonymously<br>
reported.  The dealer and the jet were found guilty.  The owner of<br>
the plane finally got his plane back by buying it at the auction.<br>
<p>
More recently the news has shifted to LA, which HiLites yet another<br>
set of concerns.<br>
<p>
The inability of the court system to push back on crime, especially<br>
in the area of drugs, seems to be building up a rather big head of<br>
steam that could backlash even more aggressively with laws designed<br>
for the "good of the majority" at the expense of individual freedoms.<br>
<p>
What about the reports on the activities of the Lord's Day Alliance<br>
and the Moral Majority (or are they still around), and other groups<br>
pushing for state support of religion?<br>
<p>
Anyone on SDAnet wish to comment further?<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
