I have not seen anyone mention that the story of the Rich Man and Lazarus <br>
predates Christ. It is known that a Rabbinic story had floated around before <br>
Christ that has the rich man in Abraham's bosom and the beggar in hell. Could <br>
it be that Jesus took a well known story and gave it a twist. His goal was to <br>
teach that being successful in this life does not garantee heaven. His goal is<br>
not to teach the correct doctrine of life and death.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
