<title>May_1992: Interpretation of Hosea 2:11</title>
<h1>Interpretation of Hosea 2:11</h1>
Dave Buxton (<i>72450.2430@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>15 May 92 18:02:26 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#40">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#40">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#40">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#40">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0041.html">Steven Timm: "Good News is No News?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0039.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Death Afterlife"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0030.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Interpretation of Hosea 2:11"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Cheryl writes:<br>
<p>
"I'm curious about how you interpret Hosea 2:11.  Hosea is clearly symbolic<br>
of the way the Lord relates to his fallen church.  This verse says, "I will<br>
also cause all her mirth to cease, her feast days, and her new moons, and<br>
her sabbaths, and all her solemn feasts."  If Sabbath celebration was to<br>
last through eternity, how do you interpret this?  The feast days, new moons,<br>
and solemn feasts of Judaism have ceased.  Does this really mean that the<br>
all important sabbath, the sign of his chosen people would also cease?  Or<br>
could that the 7-day sabbath would cease?  I think Sunday-keepers would not<br>
like the first interpretation.  And 7-day keepers would not agree with the<br>
second.  So how should this be interpreted?"<br>
<p>
In context these statements apply to God rejecting His people because they <br>
have rejected Him. It does not say He will take these things away from His <br>
followers, but rather from those who have ceased to follow Him. God provided <br>
all of the things mentioned to be a blessing to His people and now He is <br>
withholding these blessings.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0041.html">Steven Timm: "Good News is No News?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0039.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Death Afterlife"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0030.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Interpretation of Hosea 2:11"</a>
</ul>
