<title>May_1992: Re: Saved or Not Saved</title>
<h1>Re: Saved or Not Saved</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 19 May 92 9:36:32 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#61">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#61">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#61">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#61">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0062.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Saved or Not Saved"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0060.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Commitment and Finances"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0046.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Saved or Not Saved"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0059.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Saved or Not Saved"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Ruben Gonzalez writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; Which do you think it would be more correct to say; when one is converted</i><br>
<i>&gt; one is saved (full stop) OR one is on the path of salvation ?</i><br>
<i>&gt; There is a very important yet subtle distinction here.</i><br>
<p>
When we get down to nuances of language, differences of interpretation, of<br>
connotation creep in, thereby increasing the likelihood that we may not<br>
all understand your wording in the same way.<br>
<p>
Permit me to rewrite your question as "Can one say the he/she has eternal<br>
life, or does one say one is on the path to eternal life?".  Let's then<br>
look at Scripture.  Using grep as the "weapon" 8-) (sword of the Spirit)<br>
to search for the occurence of "eternal" and "life" in the same verses:<br>
Nothing in the OT, but the NT includes these:<br>
<p>
MAR 10:30 But he shall receive an hundredfold now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and lands, with persecutions; and in the world to come eternal life.<br>
JOH 3:15 That whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have eternal life.<br>
JOH 4:36 And he that reapeth receiveth wages, and gathereth fruit unto life eternal: that both he that soweth and he that reapeth may rejoice together.<br>
JOH 5:39 Search the scriptures; for in them ye think ye have eternal life: and they are they which testify of me.<br>
JOH 6:54 Whoso eateth my flesh, and drinketh my blood, hath eternal life; and I will raise him up at the last day.<br>
JOH 10:28 And I give unto them eternal life; and they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.<br>
JOH 12:25 He that loveth his life shall lose it; and he that hateth his life in this world shall keep it unto life eternal.<br>
JOH 17:2 As thou hast given him power over all flesh, that he should give eternal life to as many as thou hast given him.<br>
JOH 17:3 And this is life eternal, that they might know thee the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom thou hast sent.<br>
ACT 13:48 And when the Gentiles heard this, they were glad, and glorified the word of the Lord: and as many as were ordained to eternal life believed.<br>
ROM 2:7 To them who by patient continuance in well doing seek for glory and honour and immortality, eternal life:<br>
ROM 5:21 That as sin hath reigned unto death, even so might grace reign through righteousness unto eternal life by Jesus Christ our Lord.<br>
ROM 6:23 For the wages of sin is death; but the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.<br>
TI1 6:12 Fight the good fight of faith, lay hold on eternal life, whereunto thou art also called, and hast professed a good profession before many witnesses.<br>
TI1 6:19 Laying up in store for themselves a good foundation against the time to come, that they may lay hold on eternal life.<br>
TIT 1:2 In hope of eternal life, which God, that cannot lie, promised before the world began;<br>
TIT 3:7 That being justified by his grace, we should be made heirs according to the hope of eternal life.<br>
JO1 1:2 (For the life was manifested, and we have seen it, and bear witness, and shew unto you that eternal life, which was with the Father, and was manifested unto us;)<br>
JO1 2:25 And this is the promise that he hath promised us, even eternal life.<br>
JO1 3:15 Whosoever hateth his brother is a murderer: and ye know that no murderer hath eternal life abiding in him.<br>
JO1 5:11 And this is the record, that God hath given to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.<br>
JO1 5:13 These things have I written unto you that believe on the name of the Son of God; that ye may know that ye have eternal life, and that ye may believe on the name of the Son of God.<br>
JO1 5:20 And we know that the Son of God is come, and hath given us an understanding, that we may know him that is true, and we are in him that is true, even in his Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God, and eternal life.<br>
JUD 1:21 Keep yourselves in the love of God, looking for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ unto eternal life.<br>
<p>
I note that several speak of having eternal life *right now* (1Jn5:13 being<br>
the most outstanding, but severals others in John's epistle speak equally<br>
strongly).  Eternal life is a gift (!! not earned), Rom 6:23, et al.  Paul<br>
in Titus urges us to grab hold and hang on tightly (so as not to cast it<br>
away, Heb 10:35).  It is discovered (by reading with faith) in the Scriptures<br>
and coming to know Christ as Savior *and* Lord.  It is also a promise that<br>
is fulfilled at the second coming (1Cor15:53,54).<br>
<p>
Suppose my parents were among the landed and moneyed.  Suppose at my birth<br>
they start tucking away major sums of money into prudent mutual funds.<br>
Suppose they say the money will become mine when I turn 21 years old.  While<br>
I have not received it yet, the money is most surely mine now because of the<br>
sure word of their promise that it will be mine.  (Ignoring, for the sake of<br>
the story, how even prudent investments can turn sour)  There are only<br>
three ways I could lose out:<br>
1)  They could disinherit me (but God, who does not lie, has promised not to);<br>
2)  I could die beforehand (not an issue here; temporal metaphors do not<br>
    always map 1-to-1  8-);<br>
3)  I could spurn it (in which case the fault is all mine and none of theirs).<br>
<p>
We are justified by faith in Christ's atoning/reconciling sacrifice (Hab2:4b).<br>
We are to grow in grace (2Pe3:18), sanctifying holy character (Jos3:5, Joel2,<br>
which God has pledged to do in us, Lev20:7,8, 1Th5:23, by the indwelling of<br>
the Holy Spirit, Eph3:16).<br>
<p>
Perhaps it is best summed up in the words of Hanani to King Asa:<br>
    CH2 16:9 For the eyes of the LORD run to and fro throughout the whole earth,<br>
    to shew himself strong in the behalf of them whose heart is perfect [i.e.,<br>
    whose heart holds nothing back] toward him.<br>
God is looking for people who hold nothing back from Him, who acknowledge<br>
His Lordship in every part of their lives.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola TSD (DW278), 2900 S. Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ  85282
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  For I know the thoughts that I have toward you, says the Lord, thoughts of
    peace and not evil, to give you hope and a future (Jer 29:11).
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
