<title>May_1992: Three Wavy Lines</title>
<h1>Three Wavy Lines</h1>
Dave Buxton (<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 26 May 92 07:37:16 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#81">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#81">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#81">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#81">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Three Wavy Lines"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0080.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Spirit and Soul"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0082.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Three Wavy Lines"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; Over the weekend of May 16, most of the Adventist Review staff visited</i><br>
<i>&gt; the Hinsdale, IL area.  I attended the forum that they held in the afternoon.</i><br>
. . . .<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Other side issues:  William Johnsson responded to the issue of the change</i><br>
<i>&gt; of three angels to three wavy lines:  "The three wavy lines in the "A"</i><br>
<i>&gt; of Adventist Review are three stylized angels."  No lie.</i><br>
<p>
Thanks Steve for asking the question I would have asked if I was there.<br>
Perhaps it is best to accept this as their answer, it does seem plausible.<br>
The reasons I wish they would change back is that the three wavy lines<br>
do have other meanings in other contexts:<br>
<p>
 * The three waves of the Pentecostal movement that the Pentecostals<br>
   speak of.<br>
<p>
 * Many New Agers speak of unity in diversity.  Their three wavy lines<br>
   merge together, at one end.  They merge together at one end because<br>
   the wavy lines are not parallel but draw together at one end.  The<br>
   Adbventist Review merges together because they thicken at one end.<br>
   I doubt they intended a coincidence with the New Age theme.<br>
<p>
 * Publications of the World Council of Churches that use a bold across<br>
   the page three wavy lines that mean  ____(?), Eucarist and _____.  I<br>
   wish I could remember the three.  Sounds like some of the language of<br>
   Vatican II.  A friend of mine has the actually glossy publications<br>
   from the WCC, with the comments of endorsement from the SDA delegate.<br>
   This delegate is reportedly there on his own recognisance and not<br>
   a delegate of the GC.  But his attendance and endorsement does seem<br>
   awfully inappropriate to me.<br>
<p>
OK, so the the new Adventist Review logo is coincidental graphics art.<br>
But I do wish they would get back to something that looks more obviously<br>
like three angels.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
