<!-- body="start" -->
I'm interested in this thread on tithing and church office or board<br>
membership.  This issue to me is whether or not a person supports the<br>
church financially -- not what avenue the money goes through.  If a<br>
candidate for church office or board membership does NOT financially<br>
support the church, in any way or through any avenue, then I do not<br>
believe they should hold office or sit on the board.<br>
 <br>
I have sat on nominating committees where this has been an issue and on<br>
others where it was not even brought up.  The one year we had a pastor<br>
who felt that the only proper avenue for tithe was through the conference,<br>
and he wanted that enforced through the nominating committee, I voluntarily<br>
took a sabbatical from any offices.  Notice I said voluntarily.  The<br>
problem was that the criterion was not being equally applied -- one specific<br>
person was kept out of church office and the reason was said to be due<br>
to his lack of paying tithe through the conference.  I told the committee<br>
that I had been known to pay my tithe elsewhere also, and thus should be<br>
rejected by the same criterion.  They were unwilling to do so because I<br>
did sometimes send it through the conference.  This seemed to me to be<br>
a weak defense, so I voluntarily refused office that year.  The next year<br>
all the committee asked was that the treasurer state whether or not a<br>
nominee was supporting the church financially -- no specific percentages<br>
were required, nor certain avenues of support.  That seemed a bit better.<br>
 <br>
By the way, concerning the man who was rejected from office for this reason,<br>
it was handled dismally and he didn't attend church for about 18 months.  I<br>
know, I know, our faith should be such that we continue though the heavens<br>
fall, but I must say I didn't blame him much.  A future pastor did much to<br>
help him heal -- people skills are so useful in the pastorate.<br>
 <br>
Just a war story... to let you know that this happens in other churches.<br>
 <br>
Lola Aagaard<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
