<title>May_1992: Tithing</title>
<h1>Tithing</h1>
Cheryl Berthelsen (<i>CBERTHEL@cc.utah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 27 May 1992 12:34 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#86">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#86">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#86">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#86">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0087.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Tithing"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0085.html">Lola: "tithing and church office"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
The PRIMARY and perhaps ONLY reason we are to pay tithe is because God<br>
requires it of us and those who do not pay a faithful tithe are robbing<br>
God according to Malachi.  Does God recognize our faithful tithe if the<br>
church leaders fail to use the funds as He intended?  Absolutely.  Does<br>
God NOT recognize it if the leaders sqaunder it, manage it poorly, or<br>
even embezzle?  No!  We have followed His command and paid Him what is<br>
due.  So who is responsible for the management of the Lord's money?  The<br>
appointed leaders of the church.  If those leaders seem to be failing in<br>
this assignment, are we justified in ROBBING GOD because of this?  No!<br>
Two wrongs never make a right.  Those who have been appointed to lead<br>
God's church on this earth are responsible for the use of the tithe money<br>
and will face any misuse in the Final Judgement.  Once I have specified<br>
money as tithe and given it back to the Lord, I am neither accountable<br>
or responsible for how that money is used.  Thus, it is probably not my<br>
place to question the use of that money.<br>
<p>
I think the LDS Church position on tithing is solid.  The members are<br>
held accountable for paying their own tithe and certain member functions<br>
and responsibilities in the church are partially based on whether he/she<br>
is paying a faithful tithe (i.e., keeping the Lord's commandments and<br>
living the standards of the church).  The leaders of the LDS church are<br>
responsible for managing the use of the tithe money.  It is not our place<br>
as members to question, criticize, or direct the use of the tithe money<br>
when these leaders have that specific duty and resonsibility and are<br>
accountable to God for it.  Men who are filled with the Holy Spirit and<br>
are leading the church according to God's purpose will NOT be misusing<br>
HIS funds.  If they are NOT using them appropriately, the leadership of<br>
the church will take care of the wayward leader.<br>
<p>
The problem with the SDA church organization in this matter is that there<br>
is the attitude among members that they have the right and responsibility<br>
to oversee the use of the Lord's money.  Numerous financial catastrophes<br>
have lead the members to doubt the leaderships ability to manage the Lord's<br>
church.  This is only a symptom of a much deeper problem--the lack of the<br>
Holy Spirit in the church and men putting man's purposes ahead of God.<br>
<p>
Cheryl Berthelsen<br>
cberthel@cc.utah.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
