[Cheryl Berthelsen]<br>
<i>&gt;The PRIMARY and perhaps ONLY reason we are to pay tithe is because God</i><br>
<i>&gt;requires it of us and those who do not pay a faithful tithe are robbing</i><br>
<i>&gt;God according to Malachi.  Does God recognize our faithful tithe if the</i><br>
<i>&gt;church leaders fail to use the funds as He intended?  Absolutely.  Does</i><br>
<i>&gt;God NOT recognize it if the leaders sqaunder it, manage it poorly, or</i><br>
<i>&gt;even embezzle?  No!  We have followed His command and paid Him what is</i><br>
<i>&gt;. . . . .</i><br>
<p>
What about Nehemiah 13?   Nehemiah returned to Jerusalem to find<br>
the people had largely quit paying their tithes.  He did not beat<br>
up the people for their neglect.  He looked into the matter, found<br>
the problem and cleared it up.  As soon as the people's confidance<br>
was restored they freely gave again.  The leadership do not have<br>
free license to ignore the protests of the membership and proceed<br>
to give those who protest a rough time, by leveraging the tithe issue.<br>
<p>
Some folks send their tithes directly to poor mission conferences.<br>
They do not neglect to pay their tithe.  It goes to God's work.<br>
A lot of my tithe goes to Joe Crews, none to John Osborne.<br>
To send it to the conference means a large percentage of it gets<br>
spent on the Youth Departments lavish rock music festivals.  That<br>
I cannot conscience.  I have written to the conference about this.<br>
<p>
I suspect you did not read the long list of quotes I sent you.<br>
I would not expect you to as you do not subscribe to Ellen White.<br>
But I find her statements consistent with the Bible in that we<br>
are indeed accountable to God and not to blind faith in man.  If it<br>
goes to God's work in a poor mission field then Amen!  If it goes to<br>
the conference Rock Music festivals, then that is not something for<br>
me to be held accountable for.  So I send it to the Lord's work and<br>
not that of the other camp.  As Ellen White said -- there are two<br>
store houses, God's and Satan's.  My personal conviction is that<br>
rock music festivals are connected to Satan's store house.<br>
<p>
I do very much agree that we should not refrain from tithing.<br>
I do believe we should proceed very caustiously, with much study<br>
and prayer, before we deviate from the standard plan.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
