<!-- body="start" -->
[The words of Rhonda Gaines]<br>
"For example, the crucifixion has established "Good Friday" because the jews <br>
removed Christ's body from the cross before the beginning of the high sabbath.<br>
Many, catholics, baptist, etc., assume that this means the 7th day sabbath, <br>
when actually it means the feast of unleaven bread sabbath which is a high <br>
sabbath."<br>
<p>
I believe the use of "High Sabbath" refers to when a ceremonial sabbath falls <br>
on the seventh-day sabbath. Whenever two sabbaths fell on the same day it was <br>
referred to as a "High Sabbath." This might refer to the beginning of the <br>
feast of unleavened bread falling on the seventh-day sabbath.<br>
<p>
Ed Fargusson @ Compuserve: 72450,2430<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
