<title>May_1992: Utilizing or Wishing</title>
<h1>Utilizing or Wishing</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 29 May 1992 10:58:50 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#102">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#102">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#102">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#102">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0103.html">Steven Timm: "Pathfinders:  An Investment in Pride?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0101.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Saved or Not Saved"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Another impression from the visit of Dr. William Johnsson, Adventist<br>
Review editor, to the Hinsdale area.<br>
<p>
For lunch he joined the young adults which comprise the<br>
"Twentysomething" group in this area.  We had enjoyable conversation<br>
over dinner, including hearing his description of being on the John<br>
Ankerberg show.  <br>
<p>
Near the end of the meal he made a short statement, like so many heard<br>
before, along the lines "The church is losing its young people in North<br>
America.."..blah blah blah.  This despite the fact he was in a whole<br>
room full of the very target audience he was lamenting the loss of. <br>
<p>
When are people going to wake up and see that there are lots of people<br>
who don't have any particular gripe against the church, who are ready to<br>
be used and in many cases are being used?  We don't have time to fight<br>
the establishment because we are already part of it.  If every "I wish I<br>
could convince the youth to do....." were replaced with  "come on,<br>
youth, let's go do this."  I think we would have a lot more action.<br>
<p>
Also,  there is a whole new post-Baby Boom generation of young adults.  <br>
The post-Baby Boom generation includes me (I was born in 1965) and<br>
consideration needs to be given to the different experiences and values<br>
of this generation.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
