<title>May_1992: Re: Pathfinders:  An Investment in Pride?</title>
<h1>Re: Pathfinders:  An Investment in Pride?</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 29 May 92 17:05:21 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#114">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#114">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#114">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#114">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0115.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Pathfinders"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0113.html">Dan Blake: "Love is..."</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0103.html">Steven Timm: "Pathfinders:  An Investment in Pride?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0115.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Pathfinders"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Steven Timm writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; Over the past weekend I visited the small country church that is the</i><br>
<i>&gt; home church of my parents and was my home church for five years.  On</i><br>
<i>&gt; this particular Sabbath the Pathfinders had just returned from the</i><br>
<i>&gt; Pathfinder fair.  The club from our church had been awarded the First</i><br>
<i>&gt; Prize overall at the fair.  The fact that we have a club of fifteen</i><br>
<i>&gt; Pathfinders in this town at all is amazing.  More amazing is that they</i><br>
<i>&gt; are so well-organized and </i><br>
<i>&gt; disciplined.  They showed a large panel of the various ribbons they had won,</i><br>
<i>&gt; most of them first prizes.  Several pictures were snapped, various</i><br>
<i>&gt; medals were awarded to some of the Pathfinders, and the Pathfinder</i><br>
<i>&gt; leader spent several minutes telling us how proud we should be of our</i><br>
<i>&gt; Pathfinders.</i><br>
<p>
I have cautions about competitions in general, esp competitions in church<br>
activities.  Pathfinders is not the only area.  Colporteur sales awards<br>
are another area I have reservations on.  Btw, I find "Pastor so and so<br>
won so many souls this year" to be reasonably similar.  All the glory and<br>
praise should go to God!  (Rev1:6; note the elders' and beasts' frequent<br>
praises elsewhere in Revelation).  We should thank God for books sold<br>
and souls won, etc.  Of ourselves, we can do nothing (Acts17:28a).<br>
<p>
So, what do we say to and about people?<br>
<p>
It is appropriate to express appreciation for people's character traits<br>
and to thank them when they have been of service.  Have Johnny or Suzy<br>
been diligent in accomplishing something?  Recognize their diligence.<br>
Have Randy or Renee been helpful, of service to others?  Recognize their<br>
service.  Who has shown patience and persistence in a difficult situation?<br>
Recognize them for that.  Someone learning to profitably use their time<br>
(Ps90:12, Eph5:16)? Etc, etc.  This is particularly important for parents,<br>
but also applies corporately.<br>
<p>
p.s.  Are there not often several first's and several second's, etc at<br>
Pathfinder fairs? I have seen such at least once or twice at the few fairs<br>
I've been to.  This, at least, mitigates some problems with competition.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola TSD (DW278), 2900 S. Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ  85282
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  For I know the thoughts that I have toward you, says the Lord, thoughts of
    peace and not evil, to give you hope and a future (Jer 29:11).
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
