Steve:<br>
<p>
She must be thinking of a different Catholic Church from the one that's<br>
been criticized loud and long by feminists for continuing to be a<br>
reactionary bastion of male domination.  It puts me in mind of the story<br>
of how Pope John Paul II, on one of his visits to America, was<br>
instructed to walk across the tarmac and kiss the women in the<br>
delegation when he got off the plane.  But he got his directions mixed<br>
up and he ended up kissing the tarmac and walking across the women.<br>
<p>
(Reader's note: this is a joke.  That's all it is.  DON'T feel free to<br>
circulate this as anything but a joke.  There are too many urban legends<br>
floating around already.)<br>
<p>
Daniel J. Drazen<br>
