<title>Jun_1993: Re: net.athiests</title>
<h1>Re: net.athiests</h1>
Dan Blake (<i>dblake@hprnd.rose.hp.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 1 Jun 93 19:28:27 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#23">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#23">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#23">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#23">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0024.html">Healy, Tammy R: "Re: Notes on the day of Penteco"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0022.html">Maurice George Ashton: "Re: Cognitive Dissonance"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0002.html">Tony Dyson: "Re: net.athiests"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Original question]<br>
2) If god is so just, good, and loving, and if god wants to save us so bad, <br>
   why doesn't he show himself to all the people in the world at once?<br>
   That's the sure way to get everybody converted.<br>
<p>
[First response]<br>
Yea this is called Satans impersonation of Christ, and boy won't<br>
the whole world be converted. !<br>
<p>
[Tony's response to first response]<br>
So why doesn't God get in first? Not that I have an answer, but I think the<br>
original question is a fair one.<br>
<p>
--------------------------------<br>
I was not planning to reply to any of these questions.  I think<br>
that with one or two exceptions, they do not even make good<br>
conversation starters, let alone merit considered answers.  However,<br>
Tony thinks that this is a "fair one," so here is my $0.02.<br>
<p>
I find no better answer to "Why did God do that?" type questions<br>
than that given by the apostle Paul in the ninth chapter of Romans.<br>
<p>
   19 Thou wilt say then unto me, Why doth he still find fault?<br>
   For who withstandeth his will?<br>
   20 Nay but, O man, who art thou that repliest against God?<br>
<p>
But for Tony (and other believers) I have another answer.  God has<br>
shown himself to all the people in the world at once.  Not only<br>
that, but at that time, all the people in the world were not<br>
tainted by sin!  Yet, Mr. and Mrs. Adam rebelled against a revealed,<br>
trice-holy God.  Their "conversion" was not the result of their<br>
experience of seeing God, but due to the mercy and grace of God.<br>
<p>
One more thought just came to me.  Jesus said in John 14:9,<br>
<p>
   He that hath seen me hath seen the Father.<br>
<p>
The word of God, sharper than any two-edged sword, has the power,<br>
by the working of the Holy Ghost, to reveal Jesus to man.<br>
<p>
Dan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
