<!-- body="start" -->
[Drew Corrigan writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; Is it possible to have God's Spirit in different amounts?</i><br>
<p>
I could be disproved, but the references in Scripture to early vs latter<br>
rain tell me that this is true.  Actual refs: Deu 11:14, Jer 5:24;<br>
spiritual refs: Joel 2:23, Zec 10:1.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Can one pray for more of the Holy Spirit? Should one pray for more of the </i><br>
<i>&gt; Holy Spirit?</i><br>
<p>
Based upon Zec 10:1, I say yes.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; What does it mean that God gave Jesus the Spirit without measure?</i><br>
<p>
Limitations are never on His account (Hos 6:3), just ours (our unbelief)<br>
(cf Mark 9:23,24; Matt 19:26/Mar 10:27/Luke 18:27).  When we confess<br>
our unbelief and surrender everything we've been holding back, then we<br>
can experience what Jesus experienced throughout His life.<br>
<p>
Note that grace is the working of the Holy Spirit in our lives, giving us<br>
the desire *and* the power, both, to live in God's will, to live in ways<br>
that honor, please, and glorify God (Eph 1, Phil 2:12,13).  (Further reading,<br>
e.g., Christ's Object Lessons chapter re leavening the dough lump.)<br>
<pre>
-- 
