[From Drew Corrigan]<br>
<p>
This is peripheral to the question Steve Timm raised, but it is something I<br>
have been pondering over lately.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; The one I am not sure of is ordination, which involves the laying on of </i><br>
<i>&gt; hands.  This follows the Biblical formula of laying on of hands and praying.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Is it in this act that a special portion of the Holy Spirit is to come </i><br>
<i>&gt; on those who are ordained?  Acts 6 doesn't indicate one way or the other.</i><br>
<p>
Is it possible to have God's Spirit in different amounts?<br>
<p>
Can one pray for more of the Holy Spirit? Should one pray for more of the <br>
Holy Spirit?<br>
<p>
What does it mean that God gave Jesus the Spirit without measure?<br>
<p>
Biblical support for any possible answers would be appreciated.<br>
<p>
Pondering,<br>
<p>
Drew Corrigan.<br>
