<title>Jun_1993: Re: Gun, Guns</title>
<h1>Re: Gun, Guns</h1>
Randall A Helzerman (<i>helz@ecn.purdue.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 3 Jun 1993 01:44:58 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#37">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#37">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#37">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#37">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0038.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: &gt; Re: Notes on the day of Pentecost"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0036.html">Tony Dyson: "Teaching aids"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0014.html">Steven Timm: "RE: Gun, Guns"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0054.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Re: Gun, Guns"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;Woody says:</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;    You only have to look to China (remember Beijing?), Russia,</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;Hitlers Germany, the 1200's etc to realize that an unarmed citizenry</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;has no freedom or control over it's destiny.  It is at the mercy of</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;the government.  The right to bear arms was specificaly included to</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;prevent that kind of abuse.  The armed free man is and always has</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;been the only guarantee of freedom, and the only thing standing in</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;the way of tyranny.......</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Now Woody:</i><br>
<i>&gt; Guns being a more recent invention (a few hundred years)..  What kind</i><br>
<i>&gt; of gun are you talking about?  The weapons technology is proceeding</i><br>
<i>&gt; along, so in a few more years, we should all have laser guns, and</i><br>
<i>&gt; maybe a little guided missile, or maybe a small pocket-sized tactical</i><br>
<i>&gt; nuclear weapon. </i><br>
<i>&gt; Do you know why?  We have to protect ourselves from</i><br>
<i>&gt; these sinister governments.  Ha! Ha! Ha!</i><br>
<p>
There is entirely too much trust of governments among SDAs.  Its been<br>
fortold that the U.S. would speak like a dragon.  <br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Len</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; [Len, if you were in Texas any period of time, you would realize that</i><br>
<i>&gt; David Koresh was but one of many who subscribed exactly to the philosophy</i><br>
<i>&gt; above, and thought it to be no laughing matter.  SCT]</i><br>
<p>
No, its not a laughing matter.<br>
<p>
So far I've stayed out of this gun ownership debate, but now I'm going<br>
to spring in because I believe that SDA's should be aware of the end-time<br>
significance of what's going on.  No, I don't mean that Koresh was the<br>
antichrist or similar silliness, I just mean that the U.S. government<br>
is drifting in a most disturbing direction and it is not hard to see <br>
how Sunday Law legislation could be inflicted soon.<br>
<p>
I'll start with some radical statements and then back them up with facts. <br>
<p>
Radical statement:  <br>
<p>
Americans need guns to protect themselves against their own government.  <br>
<p>
Facts:  <br>
<p>
1.  The people who wrote the constitution recognized this.  That is why it <br>
    was written into the constitution.<br>
<p>
    Thomas Jefferson was the one who said that the right to keep and bear<br>
    arms was for the citizens to protect themselves from the government.<br>
<p>
2.  Everybody heard about the Weaver trial going on right now?<br>
    Basically Randy Weaver is on trial for murder.  Federal Agents came on<br>
    his land and killed his whole family.  They shot first--he shot back<br>
    to try and defend himself and his kids.  Is he getting a fair trial?<br>
<p>
    You be the judge, read the following:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;forwarded from firearms-politics@cs.cmu.edu -- Bob Leone</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Note: These trial updates are summarized from reports in the</i><br>
<i>&gt;_Idaho Statesman_ and the local NBC affiliate television</i><br>
<i>&gt;station, KTVB Channel 7.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Tuesday, May 25, 1993 was the twenty-sixth day of the trial.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Synopsis: The prosecution today admitted that many of the photographs</i><br>
<i>&gt; submitted as evidence were fabricated.  U.S. Attorney Ronald Howen</i><br>
<i>&gt; assumed blame for the photographs.  Remarkably, U.S. District Judge</i><br>
<i>&gt; Edward Lodge declined a defense request to inform the jury about the</i><br>
<i>&gt; recent string of evidence problems.</i><br>
<p>
(I'll cut it off here--anybody who wants the full story just email<br>
 me and I'll send it too you.)<br>
<p>
We all would be well advised to consider the kind of government we have.<br>
It kills people, and then fakes evidence to cover its tracks.  Moreover,<br>
not even the courts will allow the jurors to hear all the facts of the<br>
case.<br>
<p>
Such a government will not hesitate to impose a Sunday law as soon as<br>
the angels stop holding back the winds of strife!<br>
<p>
Yes, evil people can commit all kinds of mayhem with weapons.  But you<br>
don't seriously think that the government is composed of all angels do<br>
you?  Why should they get all the guns?<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
