I would add that if Len had been alive in the 1700's here in America, he<br>
would have a diffrent outlook.  I can't understand how people can be so<br>
blind.  History is just loaded with example after example of atrocities<br>
imposed on unarmed citizens by an armed government.  The people who fought<br>
for the US's independence, and framed the constitution understood this all<br>
to well.  It should be remembered that the Muzzle loading musket was the<br>
"assult weapon" of the times.  Yes, technology does advance.  But the government<br>
always makes sure it stays out of the hands of the people, lest they be<br>
able to overthrow it.  I truely believe that if the framers of the constituion<br>
had been able to conceputlize a fully automatic weapon, and had been able to <br>
forsee what our government would ultimatly do, they would have worded the<br>
amendment slightly diffrently.  Such as: ....to bear arms OF ANY TYPE OR<br>
CLASSIFICATION shall not be infringed...<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
