Steve, I was just trying some dry sarcasm when I replied to Woody:<br>
<p>
*********************************************************************<br>
Now Woody:<br>
Guns being a more recent invention (a few hundred years)..  What kind<br>
of gun are you talking about?  The weapons technology is proceeding<br>
along, so in a few more years, we should all have laser guns, and<br>
maybe a little guided missile, or maybe a small pocket-sized tactical<br>
nuclear weapon.  Do you know why?  We have to protect ourselves from<br>
these sinister governments.  Ha! Ha! Ha!<br>
<p>
Len<br>
<p>
You replied:<br>
<p>
[Len, if you were in Texas any period of time, you would realize that<br>
David Koresh was but one of many who subscribed exactly to the philosophy<br>
above, and thought it to be no laughing matter.  SCT]<br>
<p>
<p>
Now Steve, I followed the Koresh affair closely.  I do not subcribe to<br>
the suggestions above.  However, Woody seems to believe that we<br>
should all be armed to protect ourselves from tyrannical governments.<br>
 My point is that if we continue this argument to its logical<br>
conclusion, there may be no end to the degree to which destroy<br>
ourselves with all these weapons we have around us - all in the name<br>
of " the constitutional right to bear arms".<br>
<p>
Let us rather be armed with the "sword of the spirit", because "he<br>
will give his angels charge over" us.<br>
<p>
That's all folk!<br>
Len<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
