<!-- body="start" -->
Strangely, I'm excited that there was a discussion about homosexuality.<br>
It is a subject that few have dared discuss openly, without "fear of<br>
association", and traditional angry argument.<br>
<p>
SDAnet shows that it is a place where even controversial issues can be<br>
discussed openly, and that faith in the character and principles of Jesus<br>
Christ are strong enough to withstand controversy.  We still haven't<br>
discussed the practical applications of dealing with homosexual people<br>
or Christians, and Seventh-day Adventist homosexuals in particular.<br>
<p>
If this happens or not, I hope that we (including myself) are at the <br>
first step<br>
in realizing that everything is not as cut and dried as purported, and that<br>
there are big issues which need to be discussed.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
