My question is simple and comes out of a personal experience.  Our purpose for<br>
existence id to witness to God's love in the hope of repentance and<br>
salvation.  If you know of someone who has had a sex change operation what<br>
should be your attitude towards witnessing to that person?  Should such a<br>
person be invited to church, or given bible studies, or exposed to the<br>
truths about Jesus?<br>
