<title>Jun_1993: Re: Notes on the day of Penteco</title>
<h1>Re: Notes on the day of Penteco</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 3 Jun 93 17:42:11 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#33">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#33">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#33">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#33">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0034.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Letter from Tang Beng Yong #1"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0032.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: Notes on the day of Pentecost"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I think the point is that if we really let God's Spirit speak<br>
to us then we won't need to rely instead on humanistic mechanisms.<br>
<p>
Our problem today is very simple, we need the latter rain, God wants<br>
to communicate to us directly through His Spirit and not through means<br>
of our own devising. But it seems that we always have some better solution<br>
than that which God has provided. He has been waiting a long time for<br>
us to realise our need of His Spirit and to seek Him earnestly. But no<br>
we have a better way that we feel more comfortable with, more in tune<br>
with our humanity.<br>
<p>
And now "Ask ye of the Lord rain in the days of the latter rain" Zech 10:1<br>
has become "let us go down to Egypt and learn psychology and such that _we_ may <br>
learn how to better communicate. God says "Not by might, nor by power but by <br>
my Spirit saith the Lord of Hosts."<br>
<p>
Instead of turning to man and the "arm of flesh" why is it we don't turn<br>
to God for the outpouring of His Spirit.<br>
<p>
Is it better plans, or more money or a better system of people control,<br>
better people, or more worship, better accountability, better equipment,<br>
or more diverse and contempory services that we need ? No, none of these.<br>
We need only one thing...God's Spirit, and until we turn away from all these<br>
other things (idols) that we put before God's Spirit and seek the outpouring<br>
of His Spirit among us we are wasting our time, and acting contrary to God's<br>
will.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
