<!-- body="start" -->
As a lifelong flatlander, I've often wondered how I would get out to <br>
any sort of mountain when the persecution started.  Besides this, to track<br>
me down electronically would be trivial.  I suspect a hand will just come out<br>
of the terminal, slap on the handcuffs, and that will be it.<br>
<p>
Do those of you who say that guns are needed to protect us in America from <br>
our own government intend to take up arms whenever the death-decree folks<br>
come after you?  Do you think it will do any good to shoot a few of them?<br>
And if you don't think you would do it in the ultimate situation, why<br>
in any other situation?  <br>
<p>
As long as we have the constitution to protect us from our own government,<br>
we are fine.  If people ever mess with the constitution, they'll probably put<br>
in gun control, too, so guns would not be available to do the job the<br>
constitution could not.  I think that at the time of the end the only thing<br>
we will be able to trust to protect us from our government is the power<br>
of God,  and that is no less true now than it will be then.<br>
<p>
Of course, we could follow the example of the old Quaker farmer who said,<br>
"Friend, I mean thee no harm but thou standest where I am about to shoot."<br>
If I were to do that, I'd most probably shoot myself in the foot or something.<br>
<p>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
