<title>Jun_1993: Re: Notes on the day of Penteco</title>
<h1>Re: Notes on the day of Penteco</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri,  4 Jun 93 09:40:09 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#44">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#44">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#44">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#44">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0045.html">Darius A. Lecointe: "Re: Sex changes (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0043.html">Steve Hix: "Re: When Big Brother comes after you"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Ruben writes:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I think the point is that if we really let God's Spirit speak</i><br>
<i>&gt;to us then we won't need to rely instead on humanistic mechanisms.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Our problem today is very simple, we need the latter rain, God wants</i><br>
<i>&gt;to communicate to us directly through His Spirit and not through means</i><br>
<i>&gt;of our own devising. But it seems that we always have some better solution</i><br>
<i>&gt;than that which God has provided. He has been waiting a long time for</i><br>
<i>&gt;us to realise our need of His Spirit and to seek Him earnestly. But no</i><br>
<i>&gt;we have a better way that we feel more comfortable with, more in tune</i><br>
<i>&gt;with our humanity.</i><br>
<p>
I guess some are assuming that using drama, parables, and diverse teaching<br>
methods is divorced from earnest prayer and relying on God.  Its probably<br>
safe to say that we all agree that imaginative outreach without prayer and<br>
Christ living and working though the speaker/leader equals nothing but form<br>
and fashion.  However, the Holy Spirit is not confined to only one method of<br>
evangelism, and the latter rain will likely be just as evasive of our limiting<br>
imaginations.<br>
<p>
You have made a good point however, what we truly need above creative<br>
or traditional outreach/witness, is to know God.  To have The Christ ruling<br>
and living out His principles and character in our lives, this is what the Holy<br>
Spirit and latter rain bring - refreshing from God.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
