<title>Jun_1993: Guns, guns</title>
<h1>Guns, guns</h1>
lsusers (<i>LSARCHER@scifac.indstate.edu</i>)<br>
<i>4 Jun 93 14:20:46 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#58">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#58">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#58">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#58">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0059.html">Steven Timm: "Heroes:  Desmond Doss, Ronald Tull, or David Koresh?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0057.html">Woody Baker: "RE: Gun, Guns"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0088.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Guns, guns"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi netters:<br>
<p>
This is going to be my final say on guns.  It is obvious to me that<br>
we may never convince each other.  However, here is my final word:<br>
<p>
When this discussion started, it seemed to emphasize merely the<br>
traditions of owning merits of owning a weapon.  As, it progressed,<br>
we began to see more of what I consider ludicrous arguments about<br>
defending ourselves against tyrannical governments, and end time<br>
persecution.  Although this may seem to be a reasonable view to some,<br>
are we really suggesting that as persecuted Christians we will defend<br>
ourselves with automatic weapons or whatever weapons our laws allow?<br>
If this is the view of some, it seems to be contrary to what the<br>
Bible and EGW suggest the nature of end-times to be.<br>
<p>
Somalia is my example of gun ownership run amok; where the limitation<br>
of weapons to the citizenry would help rather tthan hurt.  There must<br>
be controls of some sort if order and not anarchy will be found in<br>
our society.<br>
<p>
My recent post was meant to be a sarcastic response to the suggestion<br>
that all citizens should own an automatic rifle to protect themselves.<br>
I'll apologize for the attempt at sarcasm, since some fellow-netters<br>
thought that I was trivializing the discussion.  However, my view is<br>
certainly not a minority opinion.<br>
<p>
If our kingdom is of this world, then we should fight.  Since it is<br>
not,  I will never buy a gun, own a gun, or use a gun (and since I'm<br>
a vegetarian, I don't plan to do any hunting).  I respect the<br>
constitutional rights of everyone who under law desires to own<br>
weapons, but I will retain the right to do without one.<br>
<p>
Thanks for the privelege of sharing my opinion.  Cheers Woody!<br>
<p>
PS: Steve's post also presents some wisdom on the subject.<br>
<p>
**************************************************************<br>
Len M. Archer<br>
Department of Life Sciences<br>
Indiana Sate University<br>
Terre Haute, IN 47807<br>
lsarcher@scifac.indstate.edu<br>
**************************************************************<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
