<title>Jun_1993: Heroes:  Desmond Doss, Ronald Tull, or David Koresh?</title>
<h1>Heroes:  Desmond Doss, Ronald Tull, or David Koresh?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri,  4 Jun 1993 19:18:54 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#59">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#59">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#59">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#59">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0060.html">Dan Blake: "Re:  acceptance in the Lord"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0058.html">lsusers: "Guns, guns"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0066.html">Kwong-hoon Andrew Park: "Re: Heroes:  Desmond Doss, Ronald Tull, or David Koresh?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I am deeply disturbed by the tone of conversation of the pro-gun forces<br>
on SDAnet.  It is merely another reflection of the militarism that is <br>
overtaking our church, and perhaps an effect of twenty years of non-stop<br>
TV violence.<br>
<p>
When I was a kid, they pointed to Desmond Doss as an SDA hero.  He worked<br>
in the face of war to save the lives of others, refusing to touch a gun<br>
himself.  For saving 75 lives in Okinawa during the 2nd World War, he won<br>
the Congressional Medal of Honor.<br>
<p>
The youth I teach now get to read about Ronald Tull, an SDA who went<br>
to the Persian Gulf during Desert Storm to shoot.  It was clear editorially<br>
where the SDA publications stood:  Saddam was EVIL, the USA was RIGHT,<br>
let's go bomb Iraq (notwithstanding SDA believers right in the thick of<br>
bombs).  Ronald Tull "The first SDA casualty of the war" was put forth<br>
as a<br>
hero.<br>
<p>
As sickening as I find that attitude, I find the current attitude expressed<br>
by the various proponents of guns even more distressing.  Nothing said<br>
about whether it is moral or not to have a weapon of lethal force.  <br>
Nothing said about whether Christians ought to be learning to use a weapon<br>
of force against fellow man.  Only political arguments "got to defend<br>
ourselves against the government."  These are the attitude that turn <br>
SDA doctrine-spouters into David Koreshes.  It sounds like Koresh would <br>
be a hero to some of you.  He "stood up against the tyrannical development,<br>
was ready to defend his family, etc. etc.".  God help us, what are we coming <br>
to?<br>
<p>
Does the idea of self-defense have any Biblical support?  It does have some,<br>
particularly in the book of Esther.  But nobody has mentioned that.  If we<br>
want to deal with the issues of self defense or killing in the name of God,<br>
then let's continue.  But SDAnet is not the place to rehash political<br>
hubris that is peculiar to the USA.  I'm not interested in what the<br>
constitution says, I am interested in what God says.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
