Whenever I get into a discussion with a Jehovah's Witness, they often<br>
point to their belief that all war is wring, and that we should not be<br>
involved in the military.  (Interestingly, we have three Jehovah's<br>
Witnesses working for our Campus Police Department.  I am glad they are<br>
only security guards, since if I need back up, I know I could not depend<br>
on them to help, since they might have to get "violent") <br>
Anyway....................<br>
<p>
Back to the question about military involvement.  John the Baptist<br>
preached repentance.  Roman soldiers came to him to be baptized, asking<br>
what they must do to repent.  Oddly, they were never told to give up<br>
their careers as soldiers.<br>
<p>
Ray the kop<br>
