Guns and Finland:<br>
<p>
I am really surprised about the discussion of Guns and SDA, and have been telling<br>
myself reading the posts "the americans are crazy..". I do not wear guns<br>
and spent one year in the finnish army as a noncombattant. There are<br>
quite a few Finnish adventist that spent the war years 1940-45 in prison<br>
because they refused to bear weapons.<br>
<p>
I think that those who have weapons in their house  for protecting<br>
themselves (I think this will exlude hunting) are about to break <br>
the sixth commandment - in my Bible there are no exclusions in that <br>
commandment. I think one more, still more important reason for not <br>
having weapons is that when you kill a person - for any reason - you <br>
place yourself in the place of God - who only is the Lord of the living <br>
and dead. As I understand it - that was the sole reason for<br>
evil to coming into existence - Lucifer putting himself in place of<br>
the Most Highest.<br>
<p>
Ralf<br>
