<!-- body="start" -->
Randy Helzerman's response (&gt;) to my post (&gt;&gt;)<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;&gt; These are the attitude that turn </i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt; SDA doctrine-spouters into David Koreshes.  It sounds like Koresh would </i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt; be a hero to some of you.  He "stood up against the tyrannical development,</i><br>
p&gt;&gt; was ready to defend his family, etc. etc.".  God help us, what are<br>
we coming <br>
<i>&gt;&gt; to?</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Time out Steve, don't you think that's a little bit of a low blow?</i><br>
<p>
Perhaps so.  I don't suspect that anyone will start having sex with young<br>
girls and calling himself the Lamb of God just because he has a lot of guns.<br>
But I think some SDA's relate to David Koresh just as the Republican party<br>
related to David Duke.  They don't agree with his womanizing or messiah<br>
claims (just as Rep. party didn't like Duke's past in the Nazi party).<br>
But they admired him for standing up to the feds, defending his family, <br>
etc. and viewed him as a martyr rather than a self-deluded maniac.<br>
I don't think I would be exaggerating to say that there are probably <br>
many folx in Texas, including SDA's, who have similar types if not numbers<br>
of weapons, and similar attitudes to the government.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
