<title>Jun_1993: Religious liberty dangers from the new left:</title>
<h1>Religious liberty dangers from the new left:</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun,  6 Jun 1993 19:53:54 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#79">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#79">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#79">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#79">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0080.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: Letter from Tang Beng Yong #1"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0078.html">David Plaisted: "Re: Heroes:  Desmond Doss, Ronald Tull, or David Koresh?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0082.html">Darius A. Lecointe: "Re: sex changes"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Just so the fearmongers don't run out of new things to talk about:<br>
<p>
What restrictions to religious liberty could be imposed by a leftist <br>
government?  <br>
<p>
I thought about this because of a court case in which three members <br>
are suing their union because they do not want their union dues used<br>
to support abortion.  They claim religious reasons.  We could see a <br>
national health care plan soon in the United States that includes taxes<br>
to support abortion.  <br>
<p>
What about enforcing political correctness into law?  Does this have <br>
any implications?  Comments are welcome.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
