<title>Jun_1993: an extract from Steve &amp; Darius' exchange</title>
<h1>an extract from Steve &amp; Darius' exchange</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@quad4.phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 7 Jun 93 12:29:45 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#97">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#97">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#97">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#97">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0098.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Sexual Immorality"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0096.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Gun, Guns"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0046.html">Darius A. Lecointe: "Re: Sex changes (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Darius A. Lecointe writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; We teach that even if a</i><br>
<i>&gt; marriage would not have been sanctioned by God He blesses it based on its</i><br>
<i>&gt; civil legality.</i><br>
<p>
Doesn't ring a bell with me.  The closest I can come is two concepts:<br>
1) If a guy and a girl became one flesh (i.e., had sexual intercourse),<br>
then that required them to get married.  This I did hear, but it was not<br>
based upon civil law (at least in my day); and no one suggested that they<br>
then have God's blessing (as in the blessing one gets in living righteously).<br>
[The OT civil laws in this regard have broader purposes than is at first<br>
apparent to us.]<br>
2) If the one you marry is not in God's best will, you do not perforce<br>
sever yourself forever from God's grace.  Indeed, God's grace is always<br>
available to those who humble themselves under God's hand (James 4:6,<br>
1 Pet 5:5b,6).  God's amazing grace can work miracles in changing lives.<br>
However, this is distinct from the blessings that come from living in His will.<br>
<p>
God uses permanent relationships to illustrate eternal principles.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
