woody@knapper.cactus.org<br>
<i>&gt; I truely believe that if the framers of the constituion</i><br>
<i>&gt; had been able to conceputlize a fully automatic weapon, and had been able to </i><br>
<i>&gt; forsee what our government would ultimatly do, they would have worded the</i><br>
<i>&gt; amendment slightly diffrently.  Such as: ....to bear arms OF ANY TYPE OR</i><br>
<i>&gt; CLASSIFICATION shall not be infringed...</i><br>
<p>
The Second Amendment say that "the right to keep and bear arms shall not<br>
be infringed".<br>
<p>
While people almost invariably see that in terms of firearms, note that<br>
the militia of the time also used knives, swords, pikes (though not so<br>
widely as before), hatchets and so on.<br>
<p>
A number of the FF's owned their own cannon, btw.<br>
<p>
And you thought the discussion was heated before...<br>
