<title>Jun_1993: Who are SDA's</title>
<h1>Who are SDA's</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon,  7 Jun 1993 22:59:30 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#93">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#93">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#93">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#93">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0094.html">Marcus Stringer: "Selected Messages... WOW!!!"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0092.html">Randall A Helzerman: ""Arsenal" at Waco? (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
This is in response to the question of LAINIE@delphi.com<br>
<p>
We have an extensive list of 27 fundamental beliefs, which I am sending<br>
under separate cover.  But here is a list of 5 items which I heard<br>
recently proposed by Ray Tetz of the core of SDA beliefs. <br>
<p>
1)  The Bible is the word of God<br>
<p>
2)  Jesus is the Son of God<br>
<p>
3)  God loves me and has a plan for my life<br>
<p>
4)  God cares about the quality of my life here and now<br>
<p>
5)  God wants to spend quality time with me (both here and hereafter).<br>
<p>
Most of the SDA distinctive beliefs are special cases of #4 and 5.<br>
<p>
Current church membership ~7 million.<br>
About 10-15% of that in US and Canada.<br>
<p>
Let us know if you want to hear more.<br>
As you have seen, there is a wide diversity on just what SDA's do believe<br>
and I'm sure that I will hear comments from all 20 sides on the above list.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
