<!-- body="start" -->
Come on, if you did NOT know they had a sex-change operation you would not<br>
have a problem with a converted person.  Christ didn't have a problem with<br>
a prositute, an extorionist, a sneak thief (Judas), or anyone else.  He<br>
saw all people as children of God, and died for all of them.  If someone<br>
had a sex change operation(s) it makes no diffrence to God if they accept<br>
him, and give thier life to him, he takes it.  We should have the same <br>
broad tolerance.  Our limitiations are that we can't see the heart, so<br>
we have NO right to judge another.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  512-837-8317 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
