<title>Jun_1993: Re: sex changes, divorce</title>
<h1>Re: sex changes, divorce</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue,  8 Jun 1993 20:51:51 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#109">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#109">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#109">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#109">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0110.html">Steven Timm: "an extract from Steve &amp; Darius' exchange (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0108.html">Fred Christiansen: "RE: Big brother"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0123.html">Dan Blake: "Church discipline"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;I've not heard of anyone being under church discipline for divorce and </i><br>
<i>&gt;remarriage for the last ten years.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Steve Timm</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<p>
We have a situation in our church where a two times divorced male had an affair<br>
with someone's wife and after several attempts to get him off the lady, he<br>
refused.  Let me here stress that the lady was also very willing.  Anyway, the<br>
ultimate happened.  They were both disfellowshpped; the lady's husband left the<br>
church (not the denomination) and went to fellowship with a near by church. <br>
The lady subsequently sought divorce and married this "gentleman" in court - of<br>
course.  Now they are requesting baptism and the vocal members of the church<br>
will not allow it.  Those who may permit it have held their peace.  <br>
<p>
I guess the strongest argument is that "We are not going to place our blessing<br>
on someone breaking up anyone's family."<br>
<p>
So. Steve, these two people are still under church discipline and they are very<br>
regular and punctual in church also!<br>
<p>
Bill Oblitey<br>
[OBLITEY@OAK.GROVE.IUP.EDU]<br>
<p>
<p>
[I am personally acquainted with one of the parties in this dispute, but<br>
was not aware that there had been any church discipline.  I stand corrected.<br>
SCT]<br>
