David Harris<br>
<p>
I only stated my simple beliefs because too often I find SDA people state<br>
the negatives of the SDA church.  Such as, because I'm a SDA I don't eat<br>
meat, don't drink coffee, don't have sex before marriage. Far too often my<br>
friends often leave out the most important part, that God loves me and I<br>
love him.  Of course I believe the 27 fundamentals of the SDA church but I<br>
was just giving my  non-SDA friend, in my opinion the most important<br>
belief.<br>
