Jerry asks:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I'm curious.  Does "truth for our time" also apply to</i><br>
<i>&gt;Ellen White?</i><br>
<p>
The answer is: YES<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;That is, does her counsel get reduced in</i><br>
<i>&gt;impact because of time and circumstance?  Doesn't the</i><br>
<i>&gt;answer have to be affirmative as to EGW if one adopts</i><br>
<i>&gt;the affirmative to the same question for the Old Testament?</i><br>
<p>
The answer is again :YES.<br>
<p>
The problem is that we too often want to to apply her writings<br>
verbatim instead of following thew principles of truth.  That's why<br>
we still have the debate about cinema vs T.V, wedding bands or not<br>
etc.  All truth is contextual, otherwise we would still not be riding<br>
bicycles and our dress and lifestyle would resemble the Amish.<br>
<p>
