<title>Jun_1993: Seventh-day Wimps</title>
<h1>Seventh-day Wimps</h1>
lsusers (<i>LSARCHER@scifac.indstate.edu</i>)<br>
<i>9 Jun 93 22:03:43 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#135">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#135">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#135">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#135">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0136.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Helpful Reading"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0134.html">Steven Timm: "Mixed marriages"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0139.html">Tony Dyson: "Re: Seventh-day Wimps"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 From Steve:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Why don't we have the situations such as Ananias and Sapphira</i><br>
<i>&gt;happening anymore?  Judging in the NT church happened early and</i><br>
<i>&gt;often.</i><br>
<p>
Probably the "judgers" are themselves in need of judgment...pot<br>
calling the kettle black... or the act of judgment is motivated<br>
by condemnation of the individual rather than the activity.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Should it grow out of a Spirit-based authority?  I think so.</i><br>
<p>
It's the JESUS way. But with that authority goes resposibility.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;  We should be careful to recognize the difference between dumping</i><br>
<i>&gt;guilt on someone and condemning them  (bad) and thwarting the</i><br>
<i>&gt;unchecked spread of evil in the church (good). Just because we cease</i><br>
<i>&gt;condemning people does not mean that there ceases to be right and</i><br>
<i>&gt;wrong.</i><br>
<p>
Actually we should be condemning the activity rather than the people.<br>
Jesus said to Mary:  "Neither do I condemn you".  However, the fact<br>
that he continued: "Go and sin no more", indicates that right and<br>
wrong continue to exist.<br>
<p>
There is now no condemnation to those who are in CHRIST JESUS!  God's<br>
condemnation.  Condemning people is not ours to do.  If we condemn<br>
someone, could we really pray for them?  What do you netters think?<br>
<p>
<p>
**LOVE CONQUERS ALL**<br>
<p>
Len<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
 Steve Timm<br>
