<i>&gt; The phrase "God loves the sinner, but hates the sin"</i><br>
<i>&gt; is not to be found in the Bible.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; How about:  God loves you enough to accept you just the way you are,</i><br>
<i>&gt; and too much to let you stay that way.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Steve Timm</i><br>
------------<br>
Neither is your phrase or its equivalent to be found in the Bible.<br>
What you do find is:<br>
<p>
   Jn. 3:3  You are unacceptable the way you are; you must be<br>
   born from above.<br>
<p>
   Jn. 3:16  God loved unacceptable sinners so much that he<br>
   provided a sacrifice to make them acceptable--his son.<br>
<p>
   Jn. 5:14  If you would be acceptable before God, sin no more.<br>
<p>
   Rom. 5:8  God demonstrated his love toward us, in that while<br>
   we were yet unacceptable sinners, Christ died for us.<br>
<p>
Dan Blake<br>
