<!-- body="start" -->
I sat on this for several days...<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I am really surprised about the discussion of Guns and SDA,</i><br>
<i>&gt; and have been telling myself reading the posts "the americans</i><br>
<i>&gt; are crazy..". </i><br>
<p>
Yeah, probably.<br>
<p>
Along with eveyone else on earth since sin entered, I fear. :{<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I think that those who have weapons in their house  for protecting</i><br>
<i>&gt; themselves (I think this will exlude hunting) are about to break </i><br>
<i>&gt; the sixth commandment - in my Bible there are no exclusions in that </i><br>
<i>&gt; commandment.</i><br>
<p>
The Hebrew translates to "murder" in english, not "kill".  There is<br>
*some* difference in meaning.<br>
<p>
Note also: Exodus 22:1,2; Luke 22:35,36; Esther 8, 9 and 10 (I was <br>
more than somewhat startled to read this last one after a *long* time <br>
of neglecting it for other parts.)<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I think one more, still more important reason for not having weapons</i><br>
<i>&gt; is that when you kill a person - for any reason - you place yourself</i><br>
<i>&gt; in the place of God - who only is the Lord of the living and dead. </i><br>
<p>
I will have to think about this point again...but I'm initially inclined<br>
to disagree, at least partially: the majority of non-disease deaths in<br>
this country, at least, are accomplished through automobile accidents.<br>
I don't see how the statement above fits such a situation.<br>
<p>
The point of self-defense (the which I believe to be defensible) is<br>
to *stop* the attacker, not to kill him.  The problem is that<br>
*effective* methods of stopping are very often potentially-lethal,<br>
and non-lethal tools are too often ineffective.<br>
<p>
Still, a decision that should be left up to the individual's <br>
conscience.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
