<!-- body="start" -->
Maybe Steve et al are right about this discipline/judgment thing, but if so<br>
I hope I'm never involved in it. Ostracism is a terrible thing, and it can<br>
be seen every day at any primary or high school in the world. Then there are<br>
those who continue to be ostracised on into adulthood, whether it's because of<br>
race, gender/career combination, religion, appearance or whatever. There's<br>
enough loneliness and rejection in the world already without us adding to it,<br>
for whatever good reason.<br>
<p>
So I guess I must be a wimp. Well I knew that anyway. I'll allow others to<br>
take the lead when it comes to public condemnation and ostracism.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
