<title>Jun_1993: Re: Notes on the day of Penteco</title>
<h1>Re: Notes on the day of Penteco</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 10 Jun 1993 19:27:55 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#132">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#132">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#132">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#132">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0133.html">Dan Blake: "Children of God"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0131.html">Dan Drazen: "Re: Seventh-day Wimps"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0145.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Notes on the day of Pentecost"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
David,<br>
<p>
	The SDA church holds 27 fundamental beliefs.  Among them are the<br>
	1.	The Holy Scriptures, OLD and NEW are the written word of<br>
		God, and the only rule of faith.  (Sola Scriptura)<br>
<p>
	2.	There is one God:  Father Son and Holy Spirit. (The trinity)<br>
	3.	God is the creator, sustainer, source and sovereign of all<br>
		of creation.<br>
<p>
	4.	God the eternal Son became incarnate in Jesus Christ, who<br>
		died for all mankinds' sin, and gave us a perfect example to<br>
		follow.<br>
<p>
	5.	God the eternal Spirit  was active with the father and Son<br>
		in the Creation, incarnation and redemption.<br>
<p>
	6.	God created the world in 6 literal days.  The Holy Scripture<br>
		gives a full account of His creative activity.<br>
<p>
	7.	Man and woman were made in the image of God, with individual<br>
		ity, power and freedom to think and to do.<br>
<p>
	8.	All humanity is involved in a great controversy between Christ<br>
		and satan regarding the character of God, his law and His<br>
		sovereignty over the universe.<br>
<p>
	9.	In Christ's life of perfect obedience to God's will, His<br>
		suffering, death and resurrection, God provided the only<br>
<p>
		means of atonement for human sin, so that those who by<br>
		faith accept this atonement may have eternal life, and the<br>
		whole creation may better understand the infinite love of the<br>
		Creator.<br>
<p>
These are a summary of the first 9 of the 27 fundamental belifs.  These<br>
are common to most churches.  I will finish the list up later, as I need to<br>
get to work now.<br>
<p>
	Additional points.  We believe that the 10 commandments (decalog) is<br>
still binding on all christians today, including the 4th commandment that<br>
enjoins the keeping of the seventh day (Saturday) as a memorial to Gods<br>
creative ability, and as acknowlegement of his sovereignty.<br>
<p>
	We believe that the dead "know not anything".  That is when you die,<br>
you die.  There will come a resurection when the rightous go to heavan and<br>
a resurection when the wicked will be raised to see Christ glorified, then<br>
will be utterly destroyed.<br>
<p>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  512-837-8317 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
<p>
woody@knapper.cactus.org
woody@chinacat.unicom.com (temporary) is forwareded to woody@knapper
[I have the whole 27kb file already typed in if anyone wants it.  SCT]
</pre>
