[Darius says]<br>
<i>&gt; We accept as valid a</i><br>
<i>&gt; marriage between a Seventh-day Adventist and a "non-believer" even though</i><br>
<i>&gt; we will not allow our ministers to conduct the ceremony in an SDA church. </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
[and Steve counters]<br>
<i>&gt; [Again, this is a custom that is falling by the boards.  Our pastor has</i><br>
<i>&gt; performed several "mixed marriages" in our SDA church, one SDA, the </i><br>
<i>&gt; other not.  Also it is not uncommon to see SDA pastors go to churches </i><br>
<i>&gt; of other denominations to wed one SDA and one not.  SCT]</i><br>
