Randall A Helzerman says:<br>
-------------------------<br>
<i>&gt;There is entirely too much trust of governments among SDAs.  Its been</i><br>
<i>&gt;fortold that the U.S. would speak like a dragon.  </i><br>
<p>
I agree, SDAs should pay more attention to prophecy, especially these days.<br>
Some don't seem to believe it, but bible prophecy has never failed, no matter<br>
how unlikely it seemed at the time they were given.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Radical statement:</i><br>
<i>&gt;Americans need guns to protect themselves against their own government.</i><br>
<p>
The notion of fighting the government with guns.... sounds to me like a<br>
revolution or something. I can't imagine Jesus using a gun to defend<br>
Himself against the oppressive Roman government, which didn't even claim<br>
to be a democracy.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;We all would be well advised to consider the kind of government we have.</i><br>
<i>&gt;It kills people, and then fakes evidence to cover its tracks.  Moreover,</i><br>
<i>&gt;not even the courts will allow the jurors to hear all the facts of the</i><br>
<i>&gt;case.</i><br>
<p>
Practically all governments do that. Not just yours.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Such a government will not hesitate to impose a Sunday law as soon as</i><br>
<i>&gt;the angels stop holding back the winds of strife!</i><br>
<p>
Yes.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Yes, evil people can commit all kinds of mayhem with weapons.  But you</i><br>
<i>&gt;don't seriously think that the government is composed of all angels do</i><br>
<i>&gt;you?</i><br>
<p>
Of course they aren't all angels, but does that mean we as Christians have<br>
to take up arms to defend against them? Jesus and Paul lived under even<br>
worse governments than yours or mine, and they never advocated resisting<br>
them with weapons. In fact, we are admonished to obey the authorities and<br>
not to fight back. Daniel &amp; Co. were even captured and sent into exile, and<br>
faced persecuitions, but God protected them, they also obeyed the king as<br>
far as they could, not fearing his wrath when they refused to bow to the<br>
idol. What does their example say to us?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Why should they get all the guns?</i><br>
<p>
They don't wear a sword for nothing:<br>
<p>
Rom 13:1-5 1 Let every soul be subject unto the higher powers. For there is<br>
no power but of God: the powers that be are ordained of God. 2 Whosoever<br>
therefore resisteth the power, resisteth the ordinance of God: and they that<br>
resist shall receive to themselves damnation. 3 For rulers are not a terror<br>
to good works, but to the evil. Wilt thou then not be afraid of the power? do<br>
that which is good, and thou shalt have praise of the same: 4 For he is the<br>
minister of God to thee for good. But if thou do that which is evil, be<br>
afraid; for he beareth not the sword in vain: for he is the minister of God,<br>
a revenger to execute wrath upon him that doeth evil. 5 Wherefore ye must<br>
needs be subject, not only for wrath, but also for conscience sake. (KJV) <br>
<p>
Steven Tim says:<br>
----------------<br>
