<p>
<i>&gt;we will be able to trust to protect us from our government is the power</i><br>
<i>&gt;of God,  and that is no less true now than it will be then.</i><br>
<p>
It has always been so, we can see the examples in the bible.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;When I was a kid, they pointed to Desmond Doss as an SDA hero.  He worked</i><br>
<p>
Same here, PFC Desmond Doss's conduct was examplary.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;The youth I teach now get to read about Ronald Tull, an SDA who went to the</i><br>
<i>&gt;Persian Gulf during Desert Storm to shoot.</i><br>
<p>
Yes. i read his story in Signs magazine. He got hit by "friendly fire" from<br>
an A-10 warthog. If i was an SDA non-combattent conscript in the Iraqi army<br>
and he came along in his tank and blasted me to bits, that would be "friendly<br>
fire" too. And if i wasn't a Christian, well, like SDA Vietnam vetran Oscar<br>
Mathison said: "If a man is bad and i kill him, he might go to hell. If he<br>
lives he might change and become better. I cannot be responsible for his<br>
destiny."<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;It was clear editorially where the SDA publications stood:  Saddam was EVIL,</i><br>
<i>&gt;the USA was RIGHT, let's go bomb Iraq (notwithstanding SDA believers right</i><br>
<i>&gt;in the thick of bombs).</i><br>
<p>
Not to mention all the non-SDAs who will now never be SDAs. Something like<br>
eighty to a hundred thousand souls were killed in Iraq, and many more are<br>
maimed and mutilated, and we are so worked up over eighty-odd Branch<br>
Davidians killed at Waco.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;SDA doctrine-spouters into David Koreshes.  It sounds like Koresh would </i><br>
<i>&gt;be a hero to some of you.  He "stood up against the tyrannical development,</i><br>
<i>&gt;was ready to defend his family, etc. etc.".  God help us, what are we coming</i><br>
<i>&gt;to?</i><br>
<p>
The end of the world Steve, that's what.<br>
<p>
Andrew Park says:<br>
-----------------<br>
