the Times didn't say so. I thought it was just a story about some Christian<br>
serving in the Gulf, and how God preserved His life, about his faith and<br>
forgiving spirit etc.<br>
<p>
Steve Hix says to Steve Timm:<br>
-----------------------------<br>
SCT&gt; Do you think it will do any good to shoot a few of them?<br>
SCT&gt; And if you don't think you would do it in the ultimate situation, why<br>
SCT&gt; in any other situation?<br>
SH&gt;By this argument one should not resist criminal attacks such as rape or<br>
SH&gt;assaults on children.<br>
<p>
Luke 8:25 And he said unto them, Where is your faith? And they being afraid<br>
wondered, saying one to another, What manner of man is this! for he<br>
commandeth even the winds and water, and they obey him. (KJV)<br>
<p>
Matt 5:38-45 38 Ye have heard that it hath been said, An eye for an eye, and<br>
a tooth for a tooth: 39 But I say unto you, That ye resist not evil: but<br>
whosoever shall smite thee on thy right cheek, turn to him the other also. 40<br>
And if any man will sue thee at the law, and take away thy coat, let him have<br>
thy cloke also. 41 And whosoever shall compel thee to go a mile, go with him<br>
twain. 42 Give to him that asketh thee, and from him that would borrow of<br>
thee turn not thou away. 43 Ye have heard that it hath been said, Thou shalt<br>
love thy neighbour, and hate thine enemy. 44 But I say unto you, Love your<br>
enemies, bless them that curse you, do good to them that hate you, and pray<br>
for them which despitefully use you, and persecute you; 45 That ye may be the<br>
children of your Father which is in heaven: for he maketh his sun to rise on<br>
the evil and on the good, and sendeth rain on the just and on the unjust.<br>
<p>
Lk 6:27-30 27 But I say unto you which hear, Love your enemies, do good to<br>
them which hate you, 28 Bless them that curse you, and pray for them which<br>
despitefully use you. 29 And unto him that smiteth thee on the one cheek<br>
offer also the other; and him that taketh away thy cloke forbid not to take<br>
thy coat also. 30 Give to every man that asketh of thee; and of him that<br>
taketh away thy goods ask them not again. (KJV) <br>
<p>
Luke 6:35 But love ye your enemies, and do good, and lend, hoping for nothing<br>
again; and your reward shall be great, and ye shall be the children of the<br>
Highest: for he is kind unto the unthankful and to the evil. (KJV)<br>
<p>
1 Th 5:15 See that none render evil for evil unto any man; but ever follow<br>
that which is good, both among yourselves, and to all men. (KJV) <br>
<p>
Rom 12:19-20 19 Dearly beloved, avenge not yourselves, but rather give place<br>
unto wrath: for it is written, Vengeance is mine; I will repay, saith the<br>
Lord. 20 Therefore if thine enemy hunger, feed him; if he thirst, give him<br>
drink: for in so doing thou shalt heap coals of fire on his head. (KJV) <br>
<p>
SCT&gt; As long as we have the constitution to protect us from our own<br>
SCT&gt; government, we are fine.<br>
SH&gt; ...The constitutional guarantees did slave in the U.S. no good for a long<br>
SH&gt; time.<br>
<p>
So, if the constitution didn't protect you you'd take up weapons to fight it<br>
out with the government eh?  Jesus lived under enemy occupation,with no<br>
constitution or rights, yet He didn't fight Caesar.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Who was it who said "put not your trust in princes"? (The concordance in</i><br>
<i>&gt;the Bible here at work is *really* pitiful...) It's more true now than it</i><br>
<i>&gt;was then, if for no other reason than current "princes" can do more damage</i><br>
<i>&gt;that the ancients could.</i><br>
<p>
At least your "princes" don't feed you to lions for entertainment. So, if we<br>
don't trust princes, who do we trust, our guns i suppose?<br>
<p>
Ps 146:3-7 3 Put not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom<br>
there is no help. 4 His breath goeth forth, he returneth to his earth; in<br>
that very day his thoughts perish. 5 Happy is he that hath the God of Jacob<br>
for his help, whose hope is in the LORD his God: 6 Which made heaven, and<br>
earth, the sea, and all that therein is: which keepeth truth for ever: 7<br>
Which executeth judgment for the oppressed: which giveth food to the hungry.<br>
The LORD looseth the prisoners: ...etc(KJV) <br>
<p>
<i>&gt;(And if you were to look at countries who currently ban civilian ownership</i><br>
<i>&gt;of firearms, you'll find none that are completely-successful at it. In all</i><br>
<i>&gt;cases, criminals still have access to, and use, firearms.)</i><br>
<p>
Yes, thats true, look at my country, (its a metropolis of population about<br>
2.5 million), the whole of this year so far, i think there have been as many<br>
as 2 incidents of people getting shot at with guns!<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;The main notion of the Second amendment was to provide one more check on</i><br>
<i>&gt;the power of the State.  Also note that a militia could be called up for</i><br>
<i>&gt;more than just defense against foreign invasion; the first police</i><br>
<i>&gt;departments were set up with unarmed policemen who were to call out armed</i><br>
<i>&gt;citizens at need to deal with criminals, both individuals and groups.</i><br>
<p>
Yes, note that Ellen White says of the US that the government will eventually<br>
remove protection from Sabbath keepers and let their enemies kill them<br>
freely. So, it appears that it is the private gun owning citizens who will do<br>
most of the SDA hunting with guns. She also says that angels of God in the<br>
form of men of war will help protect us, so i don't think God wants us to<br>
fight with guns.<br>
<p>
SCT&gt; I think that at the time of the end the only thing we will be able to<br>
SCT&gt; trust to protect us from our government is the power of God,  and that<br>
SCT&gt; is no less true now than it will be then.<br>
SH&gt;Perhaps we should depend on prayer alone to deal with disease and injury.<br>
<p>
Of course, we must do what we can to avert danger, but to kill people, that<br>
is going too far. The ends does _not_ justify the means. To tell you the<br>
truth, if i was put in a situation where someone was going to kill me or my<br>
family and i had a gun to shoot back, i don't know for sure what i would do,<br>
but i still think that in principle at least, it is wrong to kill others for<br>
any reason at all, unless God tells us to do so.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Even Jesus gave his disciples leave to arm themselves for self-defense...and</i><br>
<i>&gt;it is equally clear that irresponsible use of them was not part of the</i><br>
<i>&gt;package.</i><br>
<p>
If Jesus told them to go around armed, why is there no record of any of the<br>
disciples going around armed, or using weapons in Acts, like Paul, who<br>
frequently faced openly hostile, persecuitive people?<br>
<p>
Matt 16:25 For whosoever will save his life shall lose it: and whosoever will<br>
lose his life for my sake shall find it. (KJV)<br>
<p>
Matt 26:52 Then said Jesus unto him, Put up again thy sword into his place:<br>
for all they that take the sword shall perish with the sword. (KJV)<br>
<p>
Paul et al were even stoned etc but God protected them; I think i remember<br>
that the reformer Martin Luther once met a man who brougt a pistol to kill<br>
him. The man asked him why he wasn't afraid, and he said that his life was in<br>
the hands of God, or something to that effect, so why should he be, and the<br>
man ran away.<br>
<p>
David Plaisted says:<br>
--------------------<br>
<i>&gt;I was disturbed at one vespers to promote non violence and non use of guns</i><br>
<i>&gt;and to have many leading members of my own church oppose me.</i><br>
<p>
Why ever would they do that? Are they supporters of violence and using guns?<br>
Is it true that in parts of the USA, even school kids use guns? It might be<br>
some sort of cultural thing in America, but i think there's too much<br>
violence, and too many guns there. Is it worth it when so many people get<br>
shot each year? Human lives are precious, Jesus died for people, whoever they<br>
are. We know the truth, we know that we are saved. If people kill us, we have<br>
nothing to worry about.<br>
<p>
May all of you have a good week ahead, and may God protect you.<br>
<p>
-beng tang<br>
<p>
Beng.Tang@f622.n600.z6.fidonet.org<br>
