[Steven Timm writes:]  [this wasn't me, it was Woody Baker  SCT]<br>
<i>&gt; David,</i><br>
<i>&gt; 	The SDA church holds 27 fundamental beliefs.  Among them are ...</i><br>
<p>
[This is Fred Christiansen]<br>
It is probably worth mentioning that the 27 fundamental beliefs document<br>
was published fairly recently.  I don't recall the rationale, at that time,<br>
for preparing such a document (the Intro gives some indication), but among<br>
objections was that the SDA church has survived, yea prospered, these years<br>
without it, so leave well enough alone; moreover, that there would be a great<br>
temptation to view it as a creed.<br>
<p>
When the decision was made (Dallas? 1985?) to go forward, the creed<br>
                           [Dallas, 1980  SCT]<br>
objection was met by stating (this is also in the Intro) that:<br>
1) The document does not pretend to cover all points of belief.<br>
2) The discussion on a given point of belief is not the be-all and end-all;<br>
   rather, an expression of the common understanding of Scripture.<br>
<p>
If there were a creed, it should be "The Bible and the Bible only".<br>
