<title>Jun_1993: Shooting at Big Brother (fwd)</title>
<h1>Shooting at Big Brother (fwd)</h1>
Randall A Helzerman (<i>helz@ecn.purdue.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 13 Jun 1993 01:55:36 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#159">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#159">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#159">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#159">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0160.html">David P. Harris: "Re: God loves you, but..."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0158.html">Ron Vyhmeister: "Dennis Grumling"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Randall A Helzerman says:</i><br>
<i>&gt; -------------------------</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;There is entirely too much trust of governments among SDAs.  Its been</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;fortold that the U.S. would speak like a dragon.  </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I agree, SDAs should pay more attention to prophecy, especially these days.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Some don't seem to believe it, but bible prophecy has never failed, no matter</i><br>
<i>&gt; how unlikely it seemed at the time they were given.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;Radical statement:</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;Americans need guns to protect themselves against their own government.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; The notion of fighting the government with guns.... sounds to me like a</i><br>
<i>&gt; revolution or something. I can't imagine Jesus using a gun to defend</i><br>
<i>&gt; Himself against the oppressive Roman government, which didn't even claim</i><br>
<i>&gt; to be a democracy.</i><br>
<p>
I'm afraid that I wasn't as clear in statements as I could have been.<br>
Let me try again.<br>
<p>
As I recall, this whole thread was started by somebody asking why<br>
Americans tolerate gun ownership when it results in so many deaths <br>
per year.  I tried to answer the best I could with the following:<br>
<p>
The reason that the right to keep and bear arms was written into the<br>
constitution was because the founding fathers wanted Americans to be<br>
able to violently overthow the government if it became too oppressive.<br>
<p>
This is a historical FACT.  You may not like that fact, but it is a <br>
fact nonetheless.<br>
<p>
BUT WAIT A MINUTE FOLKS!!!  TIME OUT!!! Just because I said a<br>
historical fact doesn't necessarily mean that I agree with it!  <br>
I too cannot imagine Jesus taking up arms against a tyrranical <br>
roman government, and I wouldn't either.<br>
<p>
*Never* in any of my posts did I advocate that *Christians*<br>
should take up arms against the government or anybody else.<br>
Personally, I believe that we should spend most of our time and<br>
efforts prepairing ourselves and our neighbors to be citizens of the<br>
kindom of heaven--and not citizens of the world.<br>
<p>
I'm sorry that my posts made most of you completely aghast.  I must have<br>
appeared to be quite the warmonger, because some of you made the statement<br>
that you couldn't imagine us as being part of the same church, and others<br>
intimated that my hero was the late Branch Davidian pyro cult leader.<br>
All I ask is that you all try and give me the benefit of the doubt, and<br>
in return I'll try to be clearer next time.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
