<title>Jun_1993: Dennis Grumbling</title>
<h1>Dennis Grumbling</h1>
Harvey Brenneise (<i>brneise@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 13 Jun 1993 12:07:43 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#164">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#164">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#164">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#164">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0165.html">Dan Gill: "TV"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0163.html">Ralf Simonsson: "Guns"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
It was announced in our Sabbath School yesterday by a member of the<br>
Vyhmeiseter family that Dennis Grumbling, member of this net (and<br>
husband of Heidi Vyhmeister and son-in-law of Werner and Nancy<br>
Vyhmeister) died in surgery in Chicago around 11:30 p.m.  I can only<br>
pass along the details that I have heard second-hand and hope they are<br>
correct.  Apparently there was some sort of complication related to his<br>
heart surgery serveral weeks ago and that he died of an anuerism in the<br>
lower abdomen.  If I hear more, I will pass the information along.  If<br>
someone else on the net knows more, I am sure we would appreciate<br>
knowing about our friend Dennis.  The family has asked that memorials be<br>
made to the organ fund at the Elmhurst, IL, SDA Church.  He will be<br>
buried Tuesday near Elkhart, IN.<br>
<p>
Dennis was a former student employee of the James White Library.  He had<br>
an MDiv degree, I believe, as well as a library degree (and was working<br>
on a doctorate at the University of Chicago).  He was employed in<br>
cataloging/technical services at De Paul University in Chicago, where he<br>
was in charge of the technical details of their online catalong (they<br>
have the same kind we do, and I had been looking forward to doing some<br>
professional kibbutzing with him about it).<br>
<p>
We join his family in mourning the loss of Dennis and look forward to a<br>
better day when we will see him again.<br>
<p>
Harvey <br>
(brneise@andrews.edu)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
