<!-- body="start" -->
Harvey,<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I have also noticed that men seem to be more threatened by male</i><br>
<i>&gt;homosexuality than women appear to be.  Is it possible that this is a</i><br>
<i>&gt;feeling of "letting down the side"?  Giving up the traditional</i><br>
<i>&gt;patriarchal dominance of women?  </i><br>
<p>
I've noticed this kind of thing too. <br>
<p>
Perhaps a woman has more to fear in a heterosexual man than a homosexual<br>
one?<br>
<p>
But my theory is that men are afraid of their sexuality - a bit. More, they<br>
are afraid of the terrible excesses that male sexuality can find: abusing<br>
wives, children, rape etc. The time I got the worst reaction out of Tony<br>
was when I told him that I'd met an old friend from school (9 yrs later) that<br>
day and found she had been sexually sexually abused by her father.<br>
<p>
It seems with that kind of thing that many men will prefer to not know and not<br>
have to think about it rather than address the issue. Its easier for me to<br>
just say "isn't that terrible" because I'm not a man....<br>
<p>
It is all very wierd but thats just a few thoughts I'd had.<br>
Raylene<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
