<title>Jun_1993: TV</title>
<h1>TV</h1>
Dan Gill (<i>dangle@netcom.com</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 13 Jun 93 20:05:58 -0700</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#165">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#165">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#165">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#165">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0166.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: SS ideas"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0164.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Dennis Grumbling"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi gang,<br>
<p>
Sorry if this is "off-thread", but I got behind on my e-mail and saw this<br>
comment:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Woody writes:</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;I turned my Tv off 7 years ago, (except for occasional news, such as</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;elections, the riots in LA, and the Waco thing).  We don't watch anything</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;with violenc in it.</i><br>
<p>
My TV burned up in 1984, wow that was almost 10 years ago.  I never replaced<br>
it.  I've since gotten married, have two kids, and believe it or not, I'm still<br>
alive!.  My wife wondered if we could live with out one.  I said "don't worry"<br>
there's nothing worth watching anyway.  Most people will respond to a phrase<br>
like that with, "well, I only watch PBS."  Yeah, right.  I am of the firm<br>
belief that no one should own one of those boxes.  It has been so long<br>
now, that I don't know what I'd do _with_ one. 8-)  <br>
<p>
My point:  More like a challenge:<br>
<p>
Don't watch it for a day, other than Sabbath, or do you watch it then too, and<br>
see what happens.  You'll have no other choice than to talk to someone.  Perhaps<br>
even to your kids. 8-)  See if you can't get along with out it.  There <br>
really isn't anything redeeming in it.<br>
<p>
<p>
dan<br>
