Create new study materials.  Use some of the Serendipity materials.<br>
<p>
Make sure your church has a number of types/styles of SS classes.<br>
<p>
Use the Serendipity Study Bible for a text and choose parts to study.<br>
<p>
Carry the discussion on at someone's home once a month.  Even though we<br>
use from 9:30 to 10:40 for SS we find it not enough.<br>
<p>
Tackle some of the big questions the traditional quarterlies haven't<br>
covered in my lifetime, e.g., creation/evolution; how we think/learn<br>
and what that means to SS and church [eppistemology]; how the SDA<br>
Christian [Christian SDA] responds to . . . (Whoops, only one "p"<br>
in the line above-- epistemology -- this program hates editing)<br>
AIDS, homosexulaity, abortion, stress/pain/surrering and death,<br>
etc.,etc.<br>
<p>
--Jerry<br>
<p>
Obviously the above is about athe "adult" SS.  I've got ideas on<br>
the other, but no recent experience.<br>
