<title>Jun_1993: Re: SS ideas</title>
<h1>Re: SS ideas</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 14 Jun 93 10:27:49 -0700</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#166">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#166">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#166">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#166">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0167.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Shooting at Big Brother (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0165.html">Dan Gill: "TV"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Jun 11,  8:17pm, Steven Timm wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; Subject: SS ideas</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I was just nominated on to the Sabbath School committee and have no idea</i><br>
<i>&gt; what I will do.  I now find it very challenging to come up with some</i><br>
<i>&gt; interesting Sabbath School ideas.</i><br>
<p>
Our church had such poor attendence at 9:30 am, with most showing up about<br>
9:45 or 10:00 that the SS "program" was done away with...in stages.  First<br>
the program proper was cut, but the song service remained (some still liked<br>
to sing prior to lesson study).  Then this too was poorly attended and was<br>
finally cut.<br>
<p>
So now we have lesson study from 9:30 till 10:30 am.  No one creates a SS<br>
"program".  After all, it was nothing more than a mini-church service (song<br>
service, scripture, prayer, special music, a talk, closing prayer) and then<br>
lesson study which never had enough time to get into the study.  I personally<br>
prefer the hour lesson study over the half hour we used to get.  Even an hour<br>
is rather short some times.<br>
<p>
If you do want the more traditional approach and want ideas for SS programs,<br>
try reading the ideas that Dorothy Watts has put together.  I think they are<br>
available at the ABC in a book or booklet format.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
Bruce G. Holm               503-685-1350      email:  bruceh@wv.mentorg.com
Mentor Graphics Corp.       503-685-7000
8005 SW Boeckman Rd.
Wilsonville, OR 97070-7777     Disclaimer:  Opinions expressed are my own!
</pre>
