<title>Jun_1993: Re: Shooting at Big Brother</title>
<h1>Re: Shooting at Big Brother</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 15 Jun 93 09:56:53 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#182">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#182">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#182">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#182">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0183.html">Maurice George Ashton: "Re: Guns Guns"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0181.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Guns"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0150.html">K-leb D'Cat: "Shooting at Big Brother"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve Hix wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;We (SDA's) put altogether too much trust in our respective governments, and</i><br>
<i>&gt;often (at least here in the U.S.) condemn others who disagree with what our</i><br>
<i>&gt;government may be doing. Sometimes the condemnation is justified, sometimes</i><br>
<i>&gt;it is not.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Don't make the mistake of assuming that anyone who disagrees with the civil</i><br>
<i>&gt;authority is preaching (or desiring) armed overthrow of that authority.</i><br>
<p>
I don't disagree with this possibility.  However, it is not incidental <br>
that what some<br>
view as the "evil" in government, is viewed as "good" by others toward <br>
that same<br>
government, even among SDA's...  Making adult gun owners, distributors <br>
and makers<br>
more responsible, and accountable is viewed in this light.  This is no <br>
different than the<br>
rules we had the Pornography industry comply with.  If we think the gun <br>
ownership<br>
issue is different because of "self defense", rules placed on manufacturers and<br>
distributors of the above mentioned material, were for the self defense <br>
of children,<br>
women, and the family.<br>
<p>
So, we agree that one's right to own a gun need not, be taken away by <br>
regulating<br>
the gun industry - correct?  Is there more than one way? What are they, <br>
if there are?<br>
What should Christians be doing in support of these ways?  Are there <br>
underlying issues<br>
involved in gun "misuse"?  If so, what are they, and should Christians <br>
be interested in<br>
addressing these issues?<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
