Carnegie Mellon has decided to abolish its Bitnet connection on<br>
one week's notice.  This may mean that there will be a period of time<br>
where I will not be recognized as the listowner of SDA-L, or even be able<br>
to post.  We can work it out eventually, but there may be some interruptions.<br>
The most important consequence (and this goes for SDA-L and SDAnet) is<br>
that ANDREW will no longer be in the maps as a Bitnet node and so<br>
Bitnet-only users will have to bounce off of a gateway.  Use<br>
the Internet address st0o@andrew.cmu.edu to reach me if you can.<br>
If you have to bounce off a gateway because you only have Bitnet,<br>
I will try to let you know how to do so.<br>
<p>
for instance, for Bitnet only users<br>
<p>
st0o%andrew.cmu.edu@MITVMA   should work.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
