<!-- body="start" -->
Sorry to "see" Sue leave.  A couple of years ago in the SS class I teach<br>
we spent a few weeks discussing why women are the large majority in the<br>
pews on Sabbath, but men are the large majority on the platform.  <br>
<p>
One serious problem for a church is the policy decision that our operational<br>
policies will be as near uniform as possible around the world for we are a<br>
"worldwide church."  That meant that at GC in Indianapolis North America<br>
was outvoted by the other nations on the issue of the ordination of women.<br>
One might ask, "Why assume that was a GC policy decision?" but once it was<br>
decided that it was a GC decision to make, then North America was outvoted.<br>
<p>
--Jerry<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
