To Steve and SDANET<br>
<p>
Thank all of you for your kindness at this time.  Dennis was buried yesterday<br>
in his family's plot in South Whitley, Indiana.  He is at rest in the glorious<br>
hope.  When he could no longer talk because of the intubation, he kept pointing<br>
up--his faith was strong.<br>
<p>
A group of librarians got together to set up a scholarship fund in his memory.<br>
Indiana University Foundation<br>
Dennis K. Grumling Memorial<br>
P.O. Box 500<br>
Bloomington, IN 47402.<br>
<p>
The testimony of his library colleagues at the memorial service brought out<br>
clearly that the best way of witnessing is with one's life.  Dennis did not<br>
live in vain.  He touched many others and shared love and warmth--along with a<br>
good dose of humor.<br>
<p>
We grieve not as those who have no hope.  I am making copies of all e-mail <br>
messages for Heidi.      God help us all to live for Him so that if we must<br>
die we can do so in peace.  An experience such as this serves to put life <br>
into perspective.<br>
<p>
Nancy Vyhmeister<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
