<!-- name="Fred Christiansen" -->
<!-- email="fredch@quad4.phx.mcd.mot.com" -->
<!-- subject="some tho'ts on prophecy and certainty in Scripture" -->
<!-- id="9306161927.AA08725@quad4.phx.mcd.mot.com" -->
<!-- inreplyto="" -->
<title>Jun_1993: some tho'ts on prophecy and certainty in Scripture</title>
<h1>some tho'ts on prophecy and certainty in Scripture</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@quad4.phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 16 Jun 93 12:27:16 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#190">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#190">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#190">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#190">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0191.html">TracyAnne Burtch-Nickless: "Re: Animal Sacrifice Supreme Court decision"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0189.html">David P. Harris: "Pilot Study"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Some recent postings on the relevance of Bible prophecy and what one can<br>
or cannot know motivated me to reflect on certain passages of Scripture.<br>
I'd like to share them.  And since it's just a sharing, this missive is<br>
not intended as a rebuttal, nor does it pretend to be a "tour de force".<br>
{some words below capitalized by me for emphasis; my comments in braces}<br>
<p>
PSA 19:7 The law of the LORD is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony<br>
  of the LORD is SURE, making wise the simple.<br>
  {see also Psa 93:5, 111:7)<br>
<p>
AMOS 3:7 Surely the Lord GOD will do nothing, but HE REVEALETH HIS SECRET<br>
  unto his servants the prophets.<br>
PE2 1:19,20 We have also a more SURE WORD OF PROPHECY; whereunto ye do well<br>
  that ye take heed, as unto a light that shineth in a dark place, until the<br>
  day dawn, and the day star arise in your hearts:  Knowing this first, that<br>
  no prophecy of the scripture is of any private interpretation.<br>
<p>
DEU 29:29 The secret things belong unto the LORD our God: but THOSE THINGS<br>
  WHICH ARE REVEALED BELONG UNTO US and to our children for ever, that we may<br>
  do all the words of this law.<br>
DAN 2:28 But there is a GOD in heaven that REVEALETH SECRETS, and maketh known<br>
  to the king Nebuchadnezzar WHAT SHALL BE IN THE LATTER DAYS. Thy dream, and<br>
  the visions of thy head upon thy bed, are these;<br>
  {see also Matt 16:17, 1 Cor 2:10 and on, Eph 3:5}<br>
<p>
GEN 15:13 And he said unto Abram, Know of a surety that thy seed shall be a<br>
  stranger in a land that is not their's, and shall serve them; and they shall<br>
  afflict them four hundred years; {this prophecy was fulfilled to the very day}<br>
PRO 1:23 Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you,<br>
  I WILL MAKE KNOWN MY WORDS UNTO YOU.<br>
PRO 9:10 The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom: and the knowledge<br>
  of the holy is understanding. {also Prov 1:7}<br>
PRO 22:20,21 Have not I written to thee excellent things in counsels and<br>
  knowledge, That I might make thee KNOW THE CERTAINTY OF the words of TRUTH;<br>
  that thou mightest answer the words of truth to them that send unto thee?<br>
JER 33:3 Call unto me, and I will answer thee, and SHEW THEE great and mighty<br>
  things, which thou knowest not.<br>
ACT 2:28 Thou hast MADE KNOWN to me the ways of life; thou shalt make me full<br>
  of joy with thy countenance.<br>
PE2 1:16 For WE HAVE NOT FOLLOWED CUNNINGLY DEVISED FABLES, when we made<br>
  known unto you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but were<br>
  eyewitnesses of his majesty.<br>
JO1 5:13 These things have I written unto you that believe on the name of the<br>
  Son of God; that ye MAY KNOW THAT YE HAVE ETERNAL LIFE, and that ye may<br>
  believe on the name of the Son of God.<br>
  {see also Num 12:6, Psa 51:6, Eccl 2:6, Isa 11:2, 42:16, Jer 24:7, Dan 7:16,<br>
  Hos 4:6, John 7:17, 10:14,27, 15:15, Acts 2:28, 1 Cor 13:9, Eph 1:9,17}<br>
<p>
PSA 91:4 He shall cover thee with his feathers, and under his wings shalt thou<br>
  trust: HIS TRUTH shall be thy shield and buckler.<br>
JER 33:6 Behold, I will bring it health and cure, and I will cure them, and<br>
  will REVEAL UNTO THEM the abundance of peace and TRUTH.<br>
JOH 8:32 AND YE SHALL KNOW THE TRUTH, AND THE TRUTH SHALL MAKE YOU FREE. {!!!}<br>
JOH 16:13 Howbeit when he, the Spirit of truth, is come, he will GUIDE YOU<br>
  INTO ALL TRUTH: for he shall not speak of himself; but whatsoever he shall<br>
  hear, that shall he speak: and he will shew you things to come.<br>
  {see also Isa 61:8, John 14:17, 17:17, 1 Thes 2:13, 2 Tim 2:15}<br>
<p>
DAN 12:4 But thou, O Daniel, shut up the words, and seal the book, even TO THE<br>
  TIME OF THE END: many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall be increased.<br>
  {see also Isa 46:10, Dan 8:19, 12:9, Hab 2:3, 2 Tim 4:3}<br>
<p>
Therefore, on the testimony of Scripture:<br>
* We can read, understand, and know the Scriptures, including the prophecies.<br>
  They are _not_ enigmatic; they are understandable.  One of the great<br>
  achievements of the Reformation was to wrest the Scriptures from the<br>
  province of prelates and theologians so that even a common plough-boy<br>
  could read and understand Scripture.<br>
* The prophecies are written for us; they show that God cares about us.<br>
* God would not have us be ignorant (note numerous NT refs, e.g., I Th 4:13).<br>
* The Holy Spirit leads us into truth; anyone without the HS will be led<br>
  into error.  It is the unction of the Spirit that fits one for sound<br>
  preaching; no measure of scholastic training can accomplish that (note<br>
  repeated EGW comments in this regard; note that she says sound training<br>
  plus the unction of the Holy Spirit is a very good thing).<br>
* It is, at best, unkind to compare those who study prophecy with David<br>
  Koresh.  Koresh was foolish, unmindful of such verses as 1 Cor 2:13,<br>
  Isa 28:10, et al, and showed himself an example of 2 Pet 3:16.<br>
* 1843/1844 was _not_ a fiasco.  We should not be ashamed.  It was a clear<br>
  demonstration of the principle in Psa 119:105 and of God's patience.<br>
  He gives enough light for one step.  If that step is taken, He gives<br>
  enough light to take the next step.  How foolish and arrogant of us to<br>
  make light of God's leading!  And what of us, to whom much light has been<br>
  given (cf Luke 12:48)?<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
