<!-- body="start" -->
The impressionI got from the comments was that the author has an<br>
axe to grind but has some good evidence to present.  My view is that<br>
if he has an axe to grind you should also be suspicious of the way<br>
he presents the evidence.  One of my former SDA pastors once sent me a<br>
bunch of supposedly outlandish EGW quotes in an attempt to discredit her.<br>
On reflection, I found that the great majority of them were easy<br>
to explain.  HOwever, had I been weaker in faith, it could have<br>
led me to lose confidence inher prophetic gift altogether.  I'd<br>
encourage people to avoid biased sources unless they have a need to<br>
read them.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
