<title>Jun_1993: From one of the 17</title>
<h1>From one of the 17</h1>
<i>HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU</i><br>
<i>Mon, 21 Jun 1993 10:40:58 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#220">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#220">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#220">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#220">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0221.html">lsusers: "Truth for our time"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0219.html">McCluskey G: "SDAnet and women"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
As one of the minority 17 women on this net, I must say<br>
that my absence from many discussions on SDAnet is a result<br>
of very practical reasons: I am very busy concentrating on<br>
an intense doctoral program and am now studying for my<br>
comprehensive exams in July (Prayers, please!!). It has<br>
been a lack of time, not a lack of iterest in the technological<br>
or political topics discussed here. <br>
<p>
Before I heard of the net, sought it out and subscribed, I<br>
was a lonely graduate student missing very much a link to<br>
intellectually stimulating discussions about church-related<br>
issues. SDAnet has filled a big empty spot in my life and has<br>
been my link to the church for two years. I am very grateful.<br>
<p>
It has been a traumatic time in my academic career. My<br>
dissertation topic has been in jeopardy from faculty and<br>
from other students despite my discretion about discussing<br>
it. As a result, I have testified before faculty affairs<br>
committee, met with graduate officials, etc. The University<br>
has been very supportive throughout this ordeal. Being on<br>
this side of academic plagarism gives one a very compelling<br>
view of the ethics of plagarism. <br>
<p>
Thus, self-censorship regarding posting to the net has been<br>
a matter of priorities despite the fact that I have had much<br>
to say about the public relations activities and lack thereof<br>
during this fascinating time of Koresh. <br>
<p>
Thanks to Steve and the other members of the net for keeping<br>
the discussions (heated and otherwise) on the net. It is one<br>
of the ONLY places in Adventism where this kind of open<br>
dialog can be found and I am grateful.<br>
<p>
Pam Maize Harris<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
